WEBVTT

00:01.162 --> 00:06.361
<i>♫ [Guitar]</i>

00:11.071 --> 00:14.438
<i>♫ Brazil ♫</i>

00:14.542 --> 00:19.502
<i>♫ Where hearts
were entertained in June ♫</i>

00:19.613 --> 00:24.641
<i>♫ We stood beneath
an amber moon ♫</i>

00:24.752 --> 00:28.654
<i>♫ And softly murmured
someday soon ♫</i>

00:28.756 --> 00:33.523
<i>–♫ Someday ♫
–♫ We'd kiss ♫</i>

00:33.627 --> 00:36.619
<i>♫ We'd kiss ♫</i>

00:36.730 --> 00:38.630
♫ [Fanfare]

00:38.732 --> 00:40.828
[Female Chorus]
♫ Central Services ♫

00:40.868 --> 00:43.359
♫We do the work
You do the pleasure ♫

00:43.471 --> 00:47.430
Hi there.
I want to talk to you about ducts.

00:47.541 --> 00:52.205
Do your ducts seem old-fashioned,
out-of-date?

00:52.313 --> 00:55.305
Central Services's new duct designs…

00:55.416 --> 00:58.716
are now available
in hundreds of different colors…

00:58.752 --> 01:01.619
to suit your individual taste.

01:01.722 --> 01:07.490
Hurry now, while stocks last,
to your nearest Central Services showroom.

01:07.595 --> 01:11.395
Designer colors to suit
your demanding taste.

01:13.000 --> 01:19.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:30.885 --> 01:34.949
[Man] Tonight we have with us,
from the Ministry of Information…

01:34.989 --> 01:37.651
Deputy Minister Eugene Helpmann.

01:37.758 --> 01:39.720
[Helpmann]
Good evening, David.

01:39.760 --> 01:44.158
What do you believe is behind
this recent increase in terrorist bombings?

01:44.198 --> 01:46.564
Bad sportsmanship.

01:46.667 --> 01:48.897
A ruthless minority of people…

01:49.003 --> 01:53.133
seems to have forgotten certain
good old-fashioned virtues.

01:53.240 --> 01:56.474
They just can't stand
seeing the other fella win.

01:56.577 --> 01:59.173
If these people
would just play the game…

01:59.213 --> 02:01.342
they'd get a lot more out of life.

02:01.382 --> 02:04.245
Nevertheless, Mr Helpmann,
there are those who maintain…

02:04.285 --> 02:07.681
that the Ministry of Information
has become too large and unwieldy.

02:07.721 --> 02:10.985
[Helpmann] David, in a free society,
information's the name of the game.

02:11.025 --> 02:13.854
You can't win the game
if you're a man short.

02:13.894 --> 02:18.292
[David] And the cost of it all, Deputy Minister.
Seven percent of the gross national product.

02:18.332 --> 02:21.629
[Helpmann] I understand this concern
on behalf of the taxpayer.

02:21.669 --> 02:23.569
People want value for money.

02:23.671 --> 02:29.041
That's why we always insist on the principle
of information retrieval charges.

02:29.143 --> 02:32.306
<i>–[Fly Buzzing]
–It's absolutely right and fair…</i>

02:32.346 --> 02:35.643
that those found guilty should pay
for their periods of detention…

02:35.683 --> 02:40.963
<i>and for the information retrieval
procedures used in their interrogation.</i>

02:41.221 --> 02:44.285
Do you believe that the government
is winning the battle against terrorists?

02:44.325 --> 02:48.125
Oh, yes. Our morale
is much higher than theirs.

02:48.228 --> 02:51.158
<i>We're fielding all their strokes,
running a lot of them out…</i>

02:51.198 --> 02:54.234
and pretty consistently
knocking them for six.

02:56.837 --> 02:59.767
<i>I'd say they're nearly out of the game.</i>

02:59.807 --> 03:03.072
<i>[Buzzer Buzzing]</i>

03:04.044 --> 03:06.410
<i>[Buzzer Buzzes]</i>

03:06.513 --> 03:10.344
[Helpmann]… law-abiding citizens
to have to subsidize criminals?

03:10.384 --> 03:14.616
But, Mr Helpmann, the bombing campaign
is now in its 13th year.

03:14.722 --> 03:16.952
Beginner's luck.
[Chuckles]

03:17.992 --> 03:20.054
Thank you very much,
Deputy Minister.

03:20.094 --> 03:22.028
Thank you, David.

03:22.129 --> 03:24.893
And a very merry Christmas
to you all.

03:27.001 --> 03:29.563
<i>[Woman]
“Scrooge was better than his word.</i>

03:29.603 --> 03:32.731
<i>“He did it all, and infinitely more.</i>

03:32.840 --> 03:35.936
<i>–[Imitating Machine Gun Fire]
–“And to Tiny Tim, who did not die…</i>

03:35.976 --> 03:38.968
“he became a second father.

03:39.079 --> 03:43.482
“He became as good a friend
in the good old world.

03:43.584 --> 03:46.883
“And so, as Tiny Tim observed…

03:46.987 --> 03:50.320
God bless us, every one.”

03:50.424 --> 03:53.621
<i>[TV: Chattering]</i>

03:53.727 --> 03:56.190
–Are you boys giving me the runaround?
–Where are you?

03:56.230 --> 03:59.493
–[Woman Laughs]
–Step right up. This way. Hey, hey, hey, hey!

03:59.533 --> 04:01.662
Don't throw that.
That's only for long distance.

04:01.702 --> 04:03.602
–All right.
–[Horn Honking]

04:03.704 --> 04:06.500
–I'm sorry, boys, but we
haven't got any vacancies.
–Got no vacancies.

04:06.540 --> 04:09.136
–We got plenty of rooms.
–That's all right. We take a room.

04:09.176 --> 04:11.171
–All right.
–All right. We take a vacancy.

04:11.211 --> 04:13.907
–[Laughing]
–Boy, take the gentlemen's baggage.

04:13.947 --> 04:15.847
[Laughing]

04:15.949 --> 04:18.654
<i>–[Buzzer Buzzes]
–[Bells Jingling]</i>

04:19.920 --> 04:22.692
<i>–Who's there?
–[TV: Men Chattering]</i>

04:24.291 --> 04:26.589
Who is that?

04:26.694 --> 04:30.653
Father Christmas can't come
if we haven't got a chimney.

04:30.764 --> 04:33.227
<i>–You'll see.
–♫ [Music Box: “Deck The Halls”]</i>

04:33.267 --> 04:36.600
<i>[Bells Jingling]</i>

04:37.538 --> 04:39.267
[Screams]

04:39.373 --> 04:41.307
<i>[Alarm Blaring]</i>

04:50.117 --> 04:51.445
<i>–[Alarm Continues]
–[Boy] No!</i>

04:51.485 --> 04:54.191
<i>[Male Voice On Speaker, Distorted]</i>

04:55.622 --> 04:58.460
<i>–What's going on?
–[Alarm Continues]</i>

04:58.492 --> 05:00.653
No!

05:06.500 --> 05:09.206
<i>[Male Voice On Speaker, Distorted]</i>

05:14.842 --> 05:18.573
<i>–[Alarm Stops]
–[Whimpering]</i>

05:20.914 --> 05:24.845
[Clears Throat] I hereby inform you,
under powers entrusted to me…

05:24.885 --> 05:29.185
under section 47, paragraph 7
of council order number 438476…

05:29.289 --> 05:33.187
–[Muffled Murmur]
–that Mr Buttle, Archibald, residing at
412 North Tower, Shangrila Towers…

05:33.227 --> 05:36.256
has been invited to assist the Ministry
of Information with certain inquiries…

05:36.296 --> 05:38.926
and that he is liable to
certain financial obligations…

05:38.966 --> 05:44.165
as specified in council order
RB/CZ/907/X.

05:44.271 --> 05:46.233
–Sign here, please.
–[Muffled Groans]

05:46.273 --> 05:48.571
[Shouting]

05:48.675 --> 05:51.075
Where are you taking him?

05:51.178 --> 05:53.840
There.

05:53.947 --> 05:57.246
Thank you.
Same again, please.

05:57.351 --> 06:00.411
Just there.
Press harder his time.

06:00.521 --> 06:03.888
–Good.
–What is this all about?

06:03.991 --> 06:07.552
That is your receipt for your husband.
Thank you.

06:07.661 --> 06:09.857
And this is my receipt for your receipt.

06:09.897 --> 06:12.092
<i>Mrs Buttle, are you okay?</i>

06:15.402 --> 06:17.778
–Ho! Ho!
–We're Department of Works!

06:17.805 --> 06:20.638
<i>Department of Works up here!</i>

06:20.741 --> 06:23.381
<i>Careful with those bloody things.</i>

06:23.977 --> 06:25.973
Don't take any notice of them, love.

06:26.013 --> 06:28.442
Don't touch me.
Why don't you just get the hell out of here.

06:28.482 --> 06:31.478
Don't you worry, love.
We'll have everything shipshape in a jiffy.

06:31.518 --> 06:35.849
–That's it. Nothing to worry about.
–Right. It's Tuttle downstairs who can worry, eh?

06:35.889 --> 06:39.186
Tuttle? His name's Buttle.
There must be some mistake.

06:39.226 --> 06:42.127
Mistake? [Chuckles]
We don't make mistakes.

06:43.363 --> 06:46.628
<i>–[Crash]
–That's bloody typical.</i>

06:46.733 --> 06:49.296
They've gone back to metric
without telling us.

06:49.336 --> 06:51.668
Mrs Buttle, are you all right?

06:51.772 --> 06:53.740
Yeah. Uh, uh—

06:53.841 --> 06:57.339
<i>–♫ [Music Box: “Deck The Halls”]
–[Whimpering]</i>

07:15.696 --> 07:17.664
<i>[Bell Dings]</i>

07:36.783 --> 07:38.751
<i>[Bell Dings]</i>

07:40.520 --> 07:42.420
<i>[Bell Dings]</i>

07:42.522 --> 07:44.490
<i>[Bell Dings]</i>

07:53.634 --> 07:56.432
<i>[Ticking]</i>

08:05.112 --> 08:07.080
<i>[Bell Dings]</i>

08:15.088 --> 08:18.546
♫ [Orchestral Soundtrack]

08:18.659 --> 08:20.627
[TV: Gunshots]

08:24.131 --> 08:26.099
“Buttle.”

08:28.502 --> 08:30.470
Buttle, Archibald.

08:30.570 --> 08:32.936
Ridiculous name.

08:34.041 --> 08:36.703
[Mutters]

08:36.809 --> 08:39.438
On the twenty-

08:39.546 --> 08:41.980
Oh, shit.

08:42.082 --> 08:44.983
–[Sighs]
–Mr—

08:45.085 --> 08:47.076
[Clears Throat]

08:47.187 --> 08:49.893
Mr Lowry, would you
step in here, please?

08:56.163 --> 08:59.894
–♫ [Orchestral Soundtrack]
–[Gunshots]

09:03.637 --> 09:05.605
<i>♫ [Stops]</i>

09:13.814 --> 09:16.044
<i>♫ [Resumes]</i>

09:16.917 --> 09:19.613
<i>–♫ [Stops]
–[Bell Dings]</i>

09:22.856 --> 09:24.790
Ah.

09:25.993 --> 09:28.928
I say, h-has anybody seen Lowry?

09:31.832 --> 09:36.462
Has anybody seen Sam Lowry?

10:11.705 --> 10:14.333
Sam.

10:21.214 --> 10:23.114
Sam.

10:37.064 --> 10:39.328
<i>[Buzzer Buzzing]</i>

10:40.434 --> 10:42.493
[Buzzing Continues]

10:50.343 --> 10:52.739
–Hello.
–[Man] Hello? Sam. Where are you?

10:52.779 --> 10:54.940
–Hello?
–It's 11:00.

10:55.048 --> 10:57.175
–What?
–11:00!

10:57.284 --> 10:59.616
–Mr Kurtzmann.
–Yes.

10:59.719 --> 11:02.313
[Chuckles]
You're up late.

11:02.422 --> 11:04.652
–It's 11:00.
–Is it?

11:06.059 --> 11:07.993
[Electronic Chirp]

11:08.095 --> 11:11.725
–[Alarm Beeping]
–Oh. The electrics here are up the spout.

11:11.765 --> 11:14.063
–I know. Look—
–Oh, yours too?

11:14.167 --> 11:17.603
–Yes.
–Oh, well, um, I'll be there as soon as I can.

11:17.704 --> 11:19.618
–Yes. Thanks. Bye.
–Hurry up.

11:30.684 --> 11:32.652
<i>[Bell Dings]</i>

11:34.554 --> 11:36.749
–Hello, Sammy.
–♫ [Jazz]

11:36.857 --> 11:39.189
What have you got to say?

11:39.292 --> 11:41.487
♫ [Continues]

11:53.340 --> 11:55.308
[Bell Dings]

11:55.408 --> 11:57.376
<i>♫ [Continues]</i>

11:59.412 --> 12:02.245
[Man On TV]
Oh, very good, Sammy.

12:02.349 --> 12:04.442
♫ [Ends]

12:13.927 --> 12:17.158
<i>[Children Chattering]</i>

12:17.264 --> 12:21.758
<i>[Man]… famous statue
pairing truth and freedom.</i>

12:21.868 --> 12:24.803
This is not the only statue—
Shut up!

12:24.905 --> 12:27.430
<i>What's this gun for?</i>

12:27.541 --> 12:31.105
This one, Sister,
is a nine-millimeter submachine gun…

12:31.178 --> 12:33.540
<i>used for close-quarter combat fighting.</i>

12:33.580 --> 12:35.909
<i>Very effective weapon.
Would you like to see it?</i>

12:35.949 --> 12:39.316
<i>♫ [Speakers: “The First Noel”]</i>

12:44.424 --> 12:46.824
<i>[Chattering]</i>

12:46.927 --> 12:49.623
–Oh.
–[All Giggling]

12:49.729 --> 12:52.357
Ooh!
[Giggling]

12:52.465 --> 12:54.433
[Chattering]

12:57.304 --> 13:00.364
<i>–[Buzzer Buzzes]
–[Electronic Chirping]</i>

13:03.677 --> 13:05.645
<i>[Steam Hissing]</i>

13:06.713 --> 13:08.681
<i>Sam!</i>

13:09.716 --> 13:12.207
Jack!

13:12.319 --> 13:14.981
–Well—
–Long time no see.

13:15.088 --> 13:17.684
–Hey.
–[Laughing] What are you doing here?

13:17.724 --> 13:20.520
I don't expect to see you
slumming it in Records.

13:20.560 --> 13:24.191
–What's the problem?
–Problem? No problem.
Everything's fine. Wonderful. Marvelous.

13:24.231 --> 13:26.359
<i>Alison's in great shape.
Kids are fine.</i>

13:26.399 --> 13:30.030
<i>I'm on Security Level 5 now,
so Mr Helpmann relies on me more and more.</i>

13:30.070 --> 13:32.766
–It's been a great year.
–You sound worried.

13:32.806 --> 13:35.902
Worried? Me?
If I'm worried about anyone, Sam, it's you.

13:35.942 --> 13:39.306
<i>I mean, look at you, Sam.
Whatever happened to you?</i>

13:39.346 --> 13:41.143
Records?

13:41.248 --> 13:44.020
<i>Sam, you were one of the brightest-</i>

13:52.525 --> 13:54.925
Sam?

13:56.730 --> 13:59.028
Uh, Jack, it's great to see you.

13:59.132 --> 14:01.259
–I'm gonna be late.
–Sam.

14:01.368 --> 14:04.264
Let a friend tell you.
Your life is going wrong.

14:04.304 --> 14:07.300
Records is a dead-end department.
No security level worth a damn.

14:07.340 --> 14:09.769
–It's impossible to get noticed.
–I know.

14:09.809 --> 14:12.369
Wonderful. Marvelous.

14:12.479 --> 14:14.709
Perfect. See you, Jack.

14:14.814 --> 14:17.611
–Give my regards to Alison and the twins.
–Triplets.

14:17.651 --> 14:21.087
Triplets? God.
How time flies.

14:23.089 --> 14:27.020
A very clear delineation of picture this has.
Adamant, mobile.

14:27.060 --> 14:29.028
[Man]
Next.

14:33.033 --> 14:35.805
<i>I want to report a wrongful arrest.</i>

14:36.536 --> 14:39.766
You want Information Adjustments.
Different department.

14:39.806 --> 14:41.768
I've been to Information Adjustments.

14:41.808 --> 14:44.971
They sent me here. They said
you have a form I need to fill out.

14:45.011 --> 14:47.206
Have you got an arrest receipt?

14:47.314 --> 14:50.078
Yeah.

14:50.183 --> 14:53.778
–Is it stamped?
–Stamped?

14:55.789 --> 14:58.849
No, no.
There's no stamp on it, you see.

14:58.958 --> 15:02.255
I can't let you have the form
until this is stamped.

15:02.295 --> 15:06.629
–Where do I get it stamped?
–Information Adjustments.

15:11.538 --> 15:13.506
[Clears Throat]

15:18.378 --> 15:20.175
It's nothing. It's nothing.

15:23.116 --> 15:25.312
<i>It keeps picking up old films.</i>

15:25.352 --> 15:27.411
That can't be right, can it?

15:27.520 --> 15:29.649
Perhaps the machine's on the blink.

15:29.689 --> 15:33.153
No, it's not the machine. There's a mismatch
on the personnel code numbers.

15:33.193 --> 15:37.857
Tuttle should have had £31.06 debited
against his account, not Buttle.

15:37.964 --> 15:41.161
–My God! A mistake!
–Well, at least it's not ours.

15:41.201 --> 15:43.169
Isn't it? Whose is it?

15:43.269 --> 15:45.931
–Information Retrieval.
–Oh, good.

15:46.039 --> 15:48.668
Yeah. See, Expediting has put in
for electrical procedures…

15:48.708 --> 15:52.338
in respect of Buttle, Archibald,
shoe repair operative…

15:52.379 --> 15:56.576
but Security has invoiced Admin
for Tuttle, Archibald, heating engineer.

15:56.616 --> 15:59.212
Oh, what a relief.
Finish your tea, Sam.

15:59.252 --> 16:01.743
What? Oh. Thanks.

16:03.123 --> 16:06.386
I don't know what I would do
if you ever got promoted.

16:06.426 --> 16:11.112
–Oh, God, don't worry about that.
–No, but if they did promote you, uh—

16:11.865 --> 16:14.361
I've told you before.
I'd turn it down.

16:14.401 --> 16:16.335
–Would you? Really?
–Really.

16:16.436 --> 16:18.904
You've been promoted.

16:23.109 --> 16:26.409
It's your mother, isn't it?
Pulling strings again.

16:31.384 --> 16:35.582
Sam, it's time for you
to grow up and accept responsibility.

16:35.688 --> 16:40.318
Your poor father would be appalled
at your lack of promotion. Ooh!

16:40.427 --> 16:44.022
Mother, I just wish
you would stop interfering.

16:44.130 --> 16:47.395
I don't want promotion.
I'm happy where I am.

16:47.500 --> 16:50.901
No, you're not.
Jack Lint is a lesson to you.

16:51.004 --> 16:54.200
He doesn't have your brains,
but he's got the ambition.

16:54.240 --> 16:56.231
You haven't got the ambition.

16:56.342 --> 16:59.272
<i>Luckily, you've got me
and the deputy minister.</i>

16:59.312 --> 17:02.542
–Mr Helpmann was very close to your father.
–Now, please, Mrs Lowry.

17:02.582 --> 17:04.675
Don't get upset.

17:04.784 --> 17:07.347
Mr Lowry, please wait in reception.
You're giving her wrinkles.

17:07.387 --> 17:09.287
–You see?
–[Sam] God!

17:09.388 --> 17:12.017
Just try and relax, Mrs Lowry.

17:12.125 --> 17:14.087
I'll make you 20 years younger.

17:14.127 --> 17:17.460
–Ha!
–Yoo-hoo, Dr Jaffe. You are a genius.

17:17.564 --> 17:20.089
Would you like to be surgeon general?

17:20.200 --> 17:22.634
I know simply everybody.

17:22.734 --> 17:25.799
Well, they won't know you
when I've finished with you.

17:25.839 --> 17:28.865
–Mmm. [Chuckles]
–First…

17:28.975 --> 17:31.136
we remove the excess derma.

17:31.244 --> 17:33.144
–So.
–Mmm.

17:33.246 --> 17:38.411
Now the flaccid tissues
under the eyes and the forehead.

17:38.518 --> 17:40.247
–Zip.
–Oh.

17:42.155 --> 17:45.488
Now, I lift…

17:45.592 --> 17:47.890
the wrinkles and the worry lines…

17:47.994 --> 17:50.557
right up into the wig,
into the hairline.

17:50.597 --> 17:52.497
[Sighs]

17:52.599 --> 17:54.711
<i>[Jaffe]
Now the template.</i>

17:56.369 --> 17:59.099
–Mercy.
–There. Now a bit of sticky.

17:59.205 --> 18:01.105
Like so.

18:01.207 --> 18:05.299
And already she's twice as beautiful
as she was before. Voilà!

18:07.180 --> 18:10.343
<i>Mr Helpmann was very close
to your poor father.</i>

18:10.383 --> 18:12.317
He was very close to me.

18:12.418 --> 18:14.318
Still is.

18:15.355 --> 18:18.418
He'll take you under his wing
when you get to Information Retrieval.

18:18.458 --> 18:21.723
–Thank you, sir.
–You'll like it there.

18:21.828 --> 18:24.023
<i>[Sam]
You're not listening to me, Mother.</i>

18:24.063 --> 18:27.260
[Alarm Blaring]

18:27.367 --> 18:30.430
<i>–[Alarm Beeping]
–[Man] What the hell is this, lady?</i>

18:30.470 --> 18:34.236
<i>–It's a present for my son. Really!
–[Alarm Stops]</i>

18:34.340 --> 18:37.798
I hope you like it.
It's very exclusive.

18:39.012 --> 18:40.912
What on earth is it?

18:41.014 --> 18:44.973
Something for an executive.
[Giggles]

18:46.119 --> 18:48.679
–[Clears Throat]
–Ah, Madame Lowry.

18:48.788 --> 18:51.560
You look exquisite today.
Merry Christmas.

18:51.591 --> 18:54.025
Hello, Spiro. Merry Christmas.

18:54.127 --> 18:56.623
–Sorry.
–Uh, you remember my son, Samuel.

18:56.663 --> 18:59.359
–Of course.
–We're joining Mrs Terrain.

18:59.465 --> 19:02.866
–Yes. The lady's waiting.
–Are we? God.

19:04.437 --> 19:06.997
This way.

19:07.106 --> 19:10.270
Mother. Mother, I thought we were
going to be able to talk.

19:10.310 --> 19:12.438
<i>–We will. We will.
–[Woman] Ida, Sam.</i>

19:12.478 --> 19:15.275
<i>–Oh, God. She's got what's her name with her.
–Yoo-hoo!</i>

19:15.315 --> 19:17.545
[Whispers]
Sam!

19:17.650 --> 19:22.451
Well, Alma. How are you?
You look wonderful.

19:22.555 --> 19:25.319
Hello, Shirley.

19:25.425 --> 19:27.916
Thank you, Spiro.

19:28.027 --> 19:30.120
–Salt?
–Not yet.

19:30.229 --> 19:32.595
Sam, happy Christmas.

19:32.699 --> 19:34.599
Oh!

19:34.701 --> 19:36.796
<i>–[Ida] So sorry we're late.
–Thanks.</i>

19:36.836 --> 19:39.270
<i>Now, Alma…</i>

19:39.372 --> 19:41.340
what are you going to have?

19:41.441 --> 19:45.271
I can't make up my mind whether
to have the number one or the number two.

19:45.311 --> 19:48.708
–What do you recommend, Spiro?
–Between you and me, madame…

19:48.748 --> 19:50.648
today the number two.

19:50.750 --> 19:54.213
Thank you, Spiro.
Shirley. Shirley, what are you going to have?

19:54.253 --> 19:58.485
Between you and me, mademoiselle,
today the number one.

19:58.591 --> 20:02.459
–Madame Lowry?
–Oh, to hell with the diet.

20:02.562 --> 20:04.791
I'm going to have a number eight, please.

20:04.831 --> 20:08.361
–A most perceptive choice
if I dare say so, madame.
–Oh, Ida!

20:08.401 --> 20:10.363
–Monsieur.
–Steak, please. Rare. Mother-

20:10.403 --> 20:13.499
<i>–Monsieur, quel numéro?
–I don't know which number. Mother, please -</i>

20:13.539 --> 20:15.969
–That one. There.
–That's fine. Thanks.

20:16.009 --> 20:18.805
–Mother, will you please listen to me.
–Alma! You wicked girl.

20:18.845 --> 20:22.008
–You've started your treatment.
–Say the number, please.

20:22.048 --> 20:25.347
–You noticed.
–You have to say the number!

20:25.451 --> 20:28.281
–Will you please go away! I'm trying to talk-
–I must tell you all about it.

20:28.321 --> 20:30.289
Number three.

20:31.524 --> 20:33.553
Mother, will you listen to me.
I haven't—

20:33.593 --> 20:35.720
<i>Numéro huit.</i>

20:36.829 --> 20:41.095
Braised veal in wine sauce.

20:41.200 --> 20:43.162
<i>–[Alma] Ooh!
–[Ida] Mmm!</i>

20:43.202 --> 20:48.299
<i>It's too exciting.
I've left Dr Jaffe and gone to Dr Chapman.</i>

20:48.408 --> 20:51.104
<i>–Numéro deux. Duck à I'orange.
–Dr Chapman? Chapman?</i>

20:51.144 --> 20:53.058
<i>–Excusez-moi.
–[Gasps]</i>

20:53.146 --> 20:55.546
–[Dog Growls]
–The acid man?

20:55.648 --> 20:59.112
Really, Ida! Just because
his techniques are revolutionary…

20:59.152 --> 21:02.386
I don't go around
calling Dr Jaffe the knife man.

21:02.488 --> 21:05.118
<i>[Spiro]
Numéro un, crevettes à la mayonnaise.</i>

21:05.158 --> 21:09.055
–I am sorry, Alma. I didn't mean to sound so—
–It's all right, Ida. It's just—

21:09.095 --> 21:13.031
<i>Steak. Numéro trois.</i>

21:14.067 --> 21:17.366
<i>Mesdames, monsieur…</i>

21:17.470 --> 21:19.495
<i>bon appétit.</i>

21:19.605 --> 21:21.800
<i>–Merci.
–Merci. [Giggles]</i>

21:21.908 --> 21:26.305
Acid, on the other hand, can be used
for such wonderfully subtle shading.

21:26.345 --> 21:28.336
–Hmm.
–Such delicate nuances.

21:28.448 --> 21:30.678
Like a Rembrandt etching.

21:30.783 --> 21:33.279
–And it is so much quicker.
–[Sam] God!

21:33.319 --> 21:36.849
If it wasn't for this
complication –the doctor says
it could have happened to anybody-

21:36.889 --> 21:38.851
I'd have had this dressing off yesterday.

21:38.891 --> 21:41.223
–Mm-hmm.
–Shirley.

21:42.428 --> 21:45.158
Salt?

21:50.636 --> 21:52.570
[Chattering, Gasping]

21:56.142 --> 21:58.702
<i>[People Screaming]</i>

21:59.746 --> 22:02.510
<i>[Explosion]</i>

22:04.450 --> 22:06.714
<i>♫ [“Hava Nagila”]</i>

22:06.819 --> 22:08.719
What were we saying?

22:08.821 --> 22:12.120
–This isn't rare.
–Oh! By the by, Alma…

22:12.225 --> 22:16.022
I saw the most wonderful idea
for Christmas presents at the chemist's.

22:16.062 --> 22:18.895
Gift tokens. Medical gift tokens.

22:18.998 --> 22:20.898
Oh, that sounds marvelous!

22:21.000 --> 22:24.497
It's good at any doctor's
and most of the major hospitals.

22:24.537 --> 22:28.064
It's also accepted
for gynecological examinations…

22:28.174 --> 22:30.636
<i>–including cesarean section.
–[Siren Wailing]</i>

22:30.676 --> 22:33.473
–Spiro.
–I'm sorry, madame. I don't know what to say.

22:33.513 --> 22:35.493
It never really happens to us.

22:35.581 --> 22:37.844
I'm going to do something
about it straightaway.

22:37.884 --> 22:41.647
Really, Sam! Why can't you
do something about these terrorists?

22:41.687 --> 22:44.784
<i>–It's my lunch hour.
–[Male Voice On Speaker, Distorted]</i>

22:44.824 --> 22:46.936
Besides, it's not my department.

22:46.993 --> 22:51.624
Actually, Alma, that was one of
the little things I've been dying to tell you.

22:51.664 --> 22:56.795
Look. Sam's been promoted
to Information Retrieval.

22:56.903 --> 23:00.805
Oh, that's wonderful!
Congratulations, Sam!

23:00.907 --> 23:04.704
Stop it! I'm not being promoted.
I'm not going to Information Retrieval.

23:04.744 --> 23:08.441
If I want you to stick your oar in, Mother,
I'll tell you where to stick it.

23:08.481 --> 23:11.041
<i>–♫ [Continues]
–[Chattering]</i>

23:12.418 --> 23:14.386
Pepper?

23:16.022 --> 23:17.922
I've gotta go.

23:18.024 --> 23:20.887
–Sam, you haven't had your dessert.
–I don't want dessert.

23:20.927 --> 23:24.390
–I don't want promotion. I don't want anything.
–Of course you want something.

23:24.430 --> 23:27.263
You must have hopes, wishes, dreams!

23:27.366 --> 23:29.732
No, nothing. Not even dreams.

23:40.279 --> 23:42.406
Sam.

24:14.413 --> 24:15.380
Sam!

24:27.226 --> 24:30.787
[Moaning]

24:34.667 --> 24:36.726
[Panting]

24:37.770 --> 24:39.761
[Sighs]

24:39.872 --> 24:42.534
–[Electronic Chirp]
–[Sighs]

24:42.642 --> 24:45.975
<i>[Alarm Beeping]</i>

24:49.782 --> 24:52.307
[Grunts]

24:52.418 --> 24:55.353
<i>–[Hissing]
–[High-pitched Whistle]</i>

24:55.454 --> 24:58.617
<i>–[Explosion]
–Oh, God.</i>

25:04.764 --> 25:07.536
<i>–[High-pitched Whistle]
–[Coughing]</i>

25:13.472 --> 25:15.406
[Coughing]

25:21.447 --> 25:23.779
Hello. Central Services?

25:23.883 --> 25:26.985
I'm at 579B, Block 19,
Northwestern Section “D”

25:27.053 --> 25:30.349
That's exit one on Green Pastures Highway
at the Orange Blossom Flyover.

25:30.389 --> 25:33.953
And I've got trouble with my air-conditioning.
It's an emergency.

25:33.993 --> 25:35.955
[Woman]
Thank you for calling Central Services.

25:35.995 --> 25:37.957
I'm sorry.
Due to temporary staff shortage…

25:37.997 --> 25:42.762
Central Services cannot take service calls
centrally between 2300 and 0900 hours.

25:42.802 --> 25:46.465
–Have a nice day. This has not been a recording.
–This is an emergency.

25:46.505 --> 25:48.868
Thank you for calling Central Services.
I'm sorry. Due to—

25:48.908 --> 25:52.204
–No. I've got to have a heating engineer.
–Thank you for calling Central Services.

25:52.244 --> 25:54.144
Oh, shit.

26:07.226 --> 26:09.353
<i>[Buzzer Buzzing]</i>

26:18.771 --> 26:20.671
Hello.

26:20.773 --> 26:23.401
<i>[Buzzing Continues]</i>

26:29.982 --> 26:32.109
–Hello.
–[Man] Hello.

26:33.152 --> 26:35.552
–Hello.
–[Man] Hello.

26:37.656 --> 26:39.749
–Hello.
–[Man] Hello.

26:41.193 --> 26:43.093
Hello. Mr Lowry.

26:43.195 --> 26:45.163
Yes. Who is this?

26:45.264 --> 26:48.700
Put the phone down
and raise your hands.

26:48.801 --> 26:50.769
What? Who is this?

26:54.273 --> 26:56.241
Nice and easy now.

26:56.342 --> 26:58.310
Nice and easy.

27:02.415 --> 27:05.187
Just keep your hands
where I can see them.

27:21.067 --> 27:23.797
<i>[Faint Rumbling]</i>

27:25.471 --> 27:27.649
<i>[Faint Rumbling Continues]</i>

27:29.141 --> 27:31.507
What -What are you doing?

27:36.715 --> 27:39.817
Harry Tuttle.
Heating engineer at your service.

27:43.622 --> 27:46.147
Tuttle?

27:46.258 --> 27:48.238
Are you from Central Services?

27:48.260 --> 27:50.353
[Scoffs]

27:54.100 --> 27:56.034
I called Central Services.

27:56.135 --> 27:58.631
Well, they're a little
overworked these days.

27:58.671 --> 28:00.832
Luckily I intercepted your call.

28:00.940 --> 28:03.704
You did—

28:04.810 --> 28:08.140
<i>Just a minute.
What was that business with the gun?</i>

28:08.180 --> 28:10.114
It's just a precaution, sir.

28:10.216 --> 28:12.116
Just a precaution.

28:12.218 --> 28:15.153
I've had traps set for me before now.

28:15.254 --> 28:17.817
And there are plenty of people
in Central Services…

28:17.857 --> 28:20.086
who'd love to
get their hands on Harry Tuttle.

28:20.126 --> 28:22.151
[Laughs]

28:22.261 --> 28:24.901
Are you telling me that this is illegal?

28:31.036 --> 28:34.900
Well, yes and no. Officially,
only Central Service
operatives are supposed to touch this stuff.

28:34.940 --> 28:36.902
–Would you hold this, please?
–Uh—

28:36.942 --> 28:39.305
But nowadays,
with all the new rules and regulations…

28:39.345 --> 28:41.373
they can't get decent staff anymore.

28:41.413 --> 28:44.376
So they tend to turn a blind eye
as long as I'm careful.

28:44.416 --> 28:47.780
Mind you, if ever they could prove
that I've been working on their equipment…

28:47.820 --> 28:50.116
well, that's a pipe of a different color.
[Chuckles]

28:50.156 --> 28:53.018
–Wouldn't it be simpler just to work-
–Would you hold this for me?

28:53.058 --> 28:56.555
Sorry. Yes. I was saying, wouldn't it be simpler
to work with Central Services?

28:56.595 --> 28:59.086
Nah! Nah. Couldn't stand the pa—

28:59.198 --> 29:01.928
<i>–[Low Rumble]
–We're getting warm.</i>

29:02.034 --> 29:05.464
–You couldn't what? Couldn't stand the what?
–Paperwork. Couldn't stand the paperwork.

29:05.504 --> 29:08.936
Listen. This whole system of yours
could be on fire…

29:08.974 --> 29:13.205
and I couldn't even turn on a kitchen tap
without filling out a 27 B/6.

29:13.245 --> 29:15.941
Bloody paperwork.
[Scoffs]

29:16.048 --> 29:18.310
I suppose one has to
expect a certain amount.

29:18.350 --> 29:21.380
Why? I came into this game
for the action, the excitement.

29:21.420 --> 29:26.619
Go anywhere, travel light, get in, get out,
wherever there's trouble, a man alone.

29:26.659 --> 29:30.656
Now they got the whole country sectioned off.
You can't make a move without a form.

29:30.696 --> 29:32.789
<i>[Hissing, Soft Rumbling]</i>

29:35.000 --> 29:36.968
<i>[Low Rumble]</i>

29:38.404 --> 29:40.372
[Mumbles]

29:40.472 --> 29:42.565
<i>[Electricity Crackling]</i>

29:43.809 --> 29:46.175
<i>[Pops]</i>

29:46.278 --> 29:48.212
[Sighs]
Found it.

29:48.314 --> 29:50.214
There's your problem.

29:50.316 --> 29:52.296
–Can you fix it?
–No, I can't.

29:52.351 --> 29:56.048
But I can bypass it
with one of these.

29:58.324 --> 30:00.292
Fine by me.

30:02.261 --> 30:04.422
<i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

30:04.530 --> 30:06.576
–Are you expecting anyone?
–No.

30:08.534 --> 30:11.059
[Shouting]

30:11.170 --> 30:14.401
–Get down!
–Wait! Wait! Will you wait!

30:15.441 --> 30:17.409
Shh.

30:20.579 --> 30:23.707
–The flashlight.
–[Whimpers] Ah!

30:25.684 --> 30:27.584
Central Services.

30:27.686 --> 30:29.586
–Central Services.
–Oh, yes.

30:29.688 --> 30:31.650
–You rang, sir?
–You rang, sir?

30:31.690 --> 30:34.053
–Trouble with your air-conditioning?
–Air-conditioning, sir?

30:34.093 --> 30:36.425
No, it's-it's-it's, uh, all right.

30:36.528 --> 30:39.588
It's, um— It's fixed.

30:39.698 --> 30:41.393
–Fixed.
–Fixed?

30:41.500 --> 30:43.400
Yes, um—

30:43.502 --> 30:45.697
I mean, it, um, fixed itself.

30:45.804 --> 30:48.434
–Oh, it fixed itself!
–Fixed itself? [Laughing]

30:48.474 --> 30:50.669
Yes!
[Laughing]

30:50.776 --> 30:52.756
Machines don't fix themselves.

30:52.778 --> 30:55.040
No, they don't fix themselves, sir.

30:55.080 --> 30:58.544
–He's tampered with it, Dowser.
–I think he's tampered with it, Mr Spoor.

30:58.584 --> 31:00.546
Sorry you've had a wasted journey.

31:00.586 --> 31:02.486
Oh, that's all right.

31:02.588 --> 31:05.117
<i>–I think we'll go have a little look.
–No, you can't.</i>

31:05.157 --> 31:07.421
I think we should.
Yes, Mr Spoor.

31:07.526 --> 31:09.858
Have you got a 27 B/6?

31:09.962 --> 31:12.453
27 B/6?

31:12.564 --> 31:14.526
–[Door Panel Rattling]
–27 B/6?

31:14.566 --> 31:16.898
<i>27-</i>

31:18.904 --> 31:20.866
Now look what you've done to him!

31:20.906 --> 31:24.933
Well, have you got a 27 B/6?

31:25.044 --> 31:27.808
Not… as such.

31:29.181 --> 31:31.081
But we'll get one.

31:31.183 --> 31:34.613
–It's all right. It's all right. It's all right.
–It's all right, then?

31:34.653 --> 31:38.050
Sorry. I'm a bit of a stickler
for paperwork, you see.

31:38.090 --> 31:41.220
I mean, where would we be
if we didn't stick to the correct procedures?

31:41.260 --> 31:43.660
We'll be back.

31:43.762 --> 31:45.821
We'll be back!

31:47.666 --> 31:50.430
–[Dowser Howling]
–It's all right.

31:50.536 --> 31:52.498
–Thanks for coming.
–[Howling Continues]

31:52.538 --> 31:54.500
We'll be back,
you bloody little bastard!

31:54.540 --> 31:57.378
<i>–Thank you.
–[Spoor] We'll show you!</i>

32:01.847 --> 32:04.475
[Exhales]
Well—

32:04.583 --> 32:07.546
Thanks, Lowry.
You're a good man in a tight corner.

32:07.586 --> 32:09.611
<i>–[Pats Back]
–Thanks.</i>

32:12.358 --> 32:14.883
Listen, um— I, uh—

32:15.961 --> 32:17.588
Well, I—

32:17.696 --> 32:20.059
I just happen to work
at the Ministry of Information.

32:20.099 --> 32:22.590
–What?
–And, uh—

32:22.701 --> 32:27.263
Well, I just happen to know
that Information Retrieval…

32:27.373 --> 32:31.002
are looking for an Archibald Tuttle,
heating engineer.

32:32.044 --> 32:33.944
You, uh—

32:34.046 --> 32:36.344
You wouldn't, by any chance—

32:36.448 --> 32:38.143
Would you?

32:39.385 --> 32:42.149
My good friends call me Harry.

32:43.455 --> 32:46.117
Information Retrieval, huh?

32:46.225 --> 32:48.557
The big boys.

32:48.660 --> 32:51.629
–[Chuckling]
–[Beeping, Whirring]

32:53.332 --> 32:55.232
What do they want you for?

32:55.334 --> 32:58.303
♫ [Humming “Brazil”]

32:59.772 --> 33:02.240
–Time to go.
–Sorry.

33:02.341 --> 33:04.809
–How's that?
–♫ [Humming Continues]

33:07.846 --> 33:11.740
Listen, you, um -you really must
let me give you something.

33:12.418 --> 33:14.386
[Bell Dings]

33:16.422 --> 33:19.755
How much will it be for the, uh—
for the work?

33:19.858 --> 33:21.758
Ah, come on.

33:21.860 --> 33:24.829
You did me a favor.
Just check the corridor.

33:26.165 --> 33:29.066
Oh. Well, thanks.

33:29.168 --> 33:32.069
Listen, kid,
we're all in it together.

33:32.171 --> 33:34.469
–Go on.
–Right.

33:39.978 --> 33:42.776
[Exhales]
Okay.

33:47.453 --> 33:49.421
All clear.

34:17.516 --> 34:20.156
I think Kurtzmann
is getting suspicious.

34:22.821 --> 34:25.551
What's playing today?

34:25.657 --> 34:27.556
<i>Casablanca.</i>

34:27.659 --> 34:32.543
<i>[Kurtzmann On Loudspeaker]
Mr Lowry, will you step in here, please.</i>

34:33.699 --> 34:35.667
<i>Lowry!</i>

34:37.235 --> 34:39.726
<i>Sam Lowry!</i>

34:46.879 --> 34:48.847
Psst!

34:51.250 --> 34:54.484
Thank God you're here.
We're in terrible trouble.

34:54.485 --> 34:56.112
Shh.

35:02.861 --> 35:05.657
–Look at this. Look at this.
–It's a check.

35:05.697 --> 35:07.597
It's the refund for Tuttle.

35:07.699 --> 35:09.599
–Tuttle?
–Mm-hmm.

35:09.701 --> 35:12.602
No, no. Buttle.
I mean Buttle.

35:12.704 --> 35:14.967
It's been confusion
from the word go.

35:15.007 --> 35:17.970
He's been overcharged for
Information Retrieval procedures…

35:18.010 --> 35:20.973
and someone somewhere
is trying to make us carry the can.

35:21.013 --> 35:24.510
Can I have a look?
I've never seen a refund check before.

35:24.550 --> 35:26.518
I'll bet it's Jeffries.

35:28.620 --> 35:30.520
Yes.

35:30.622 --> 35:33.585
He always believes that people should
pay more for their interrogation.

35:33.625 --> 35:35.525
And “B,” he loathes me.

35:35.627 --> 35:37.527
We've gotta get rid of it!

35:37.629 --> 35:39.591
Well, send it to somebody else.

35:39.631 --> 35:42.594
Better still, send it to Buttle.
After all, it's his check.

35:42.634 --> 35:45.097
I've tried that.
But look. Look at this.

35:45.137 --> 35:49.167
You see? The population census
has gotten him down as “dormanted.”

35:49.207 --> 35:52.671
Uh, the Central Collective Storehouse computer
has got him down as “deleted.”

35:52.711 --> 35:54.611
Hang on.

35:54.713 --> 35:57.175
Information Retrieval
has got him down as “inoperative.”

35:57.215 --> 35:59.244
Security has got him down as “excised.”

35:59.284 --> 36:02.080
<i>–Administration has him down as “completed.”
–He's dead.</i>

36:02.120 --> 36:04.111
Le—

36:04.222 --> 36:06.190
Dead?

36:08.093 --> 36:10.391
Well, that's awful.

36:14.299 --> 36:17.071
We'll never get rid
of the damn thing now.

36:17.970 --> 36:20.280
[Whimpering]
What we gonna do, Sam?

36:20.305 --> 36:22.205
Could try next of kin.

36:22.307 --> 36:24.207
Next of kin!

36:24.309 --> 36:26.800
–[Beeping]
–Yes!

36:30.115 --> 36:32.913
There we go.
Buttle. Veronica. Mrs

36:33.018 --> 36:34.918
Veronica?

36:35.020 --> 36:36.982
What's the number on the check?

36:37.022 --> 36:40.719
Uh, 27156789…

36:40.826 --> 36:42.726
[Beeping Continues]

36:42.828 --> 36:47.060
/074328K.

36:49.534 --> 36:51.502
Right. Into memory.

36:52.938 --> 36:54.906
Central Banking.

36:56.108 --> 36:58.576
Veronica Buttle.

36:58.677 --> 37:00.577
Mrs

37:00.679 --> 37:02.647
Deposit.

37:03.682 --> 37:06.014
♫ [Humming “Brazil”]

37:07.052 --> 37:09.543
♫ [Humming Continues]

37:12.324 --> 37:15.418
[Air Hissing]

37:15.527 --> 37:17.392
[Exhales]

37:17.496 --> 37:19.396
Thank God for that.

37:19.498 --> 37:21.398
Uh, would you like some tea?

37:21.500 --> 37:24.264
<i>–[Bell Dings]
–[Spoon Clatters]</i>

37:31.576 --> 37:35.171
There's a problem.
She doesn't have a bank account.

37:39.685 --> 37:41.653
Well, that's it, then.

37:42.688 --> 37:45.592
I might just as well
go and hang myself now.

37:45.691 --> 37:47.386
[Chuckles]

37:48.560 --> 37:53.191
This sort of thing could never have happened
before this stupid seventh-tier reorganization.

37:53.231 --> 37:57.429
That's Simmons's doing. And he and Jeffries
always sit together at lunch.

37:57.469 --> 37:59.164
Bastards!

37:59.271 --> 38:01.239
Sh— Shh. Shh.

38:02.974 --> 38:04.874
[Groans]

38:04.976 --> 38:09.975
Perhaps we could lose the thing behind
a filing cabinet or something—burn it, eat it.

38:10.015 --> 38:11.915
Look, there is one solution.

38:12.017 --> 38:13.917
<i>What?</i>

38:14.019 --> 38:16.381
Drive out to Mrs Buttle,
let her sign the back of the check.

38:16.421 --> 38:19.515
She can cash it
at the corner sweet shop.

38:20.692 --> 38:22.592
That's brilliant, Sam.

38:22.694 --> 38:24.594
I'll even do it for you.

38:24.696 --> 38:27.159
Here, authorize the check.
What's the address?

38:27.199 --> 38:28.666
Everything's in here.

38:29.835 --> 38:33.362
Uh, w-what should I do next?

38:36.074 --> 38:39.506
Pink and blue receipts.
Sign there, there and there.

38:39.544 --> 38:42.118
<i>–And sign the check there.
–Yes.</i>

38:43.281 --> 38:45.579
[Groaning]

38:46.818 --> 38:49.378
I think I've broken a bone.

38:49.488 --> 38:51.388
Look, my wrist is all limp.

38:51.490 --> 38:53.890
What a pathetic creature I am!

38:53.992 --> 38:56.153
Here.

38:56.261 --> 38:58.559
–I'll do it for you.
–[Sighs]

39:16.148 --> 39:18.048
[Exhales]
Right.

39:18.150 --> 39:20.243
I'll be on my way.

39:20.352 --> 39:22.582
<i>[Kurtzmann]
Sam?</i>

39:22.687 --> 39:25.588
<i>–♫ [Orchestral: Dramatic]
–Mm-hmm?</i>

39:25.690 --> 39:28.284
You are good to me, you know.

39:28.393 --> 39:32.591
<i>–[TV: Humphrey Bogart]
Here's looking at you, kid.
–Here's looking at you.</i>

39:32.631 --> 39:36.260
<i>♫ [Radio: Pop]</i>

39:36.368 --> 39:39.701
<i>♫ Brazil ♫</i>

39:39.805 --> 39:44.868
<i>♫ Where hearts
were entertained in June ♫</i>

39:44.976 --> 39:50.915
<i>♫ We stood beneath an amber moon ♫
♫ [Fades]</i>

39:51.016 --> 39:55.213
<i>[Radio: Announcer]
We interrupt this program to bring you news
of a terrorist bombing at the Blue Lagoon-</i>

39:55.253 --> 39:58.313
♫ [“Brazil” Continues]

39:58.423 --> 40:01.859
<i>♫ And clung together♫</i>

40:01.960 --> 40:04.895
<i>♫ Then ♫</i>

40:04.996 --> 40:08.830
<i>♫ Tomorrow was another day ♫</i>

40:09.935 --> 40:14.838
<i>–♫ The morning found me miles away ♫
–[Boys Laughing]</i>

40:14.940 --> 40:21.243
<i>♫ With still a million things to say ♫</i>

40:22.614 --> 40:25.174
<i>♫ Now ♫</i>

40:25.283 --> 40:30.220
<i>♫ When twilight dims the sky above ♫</i>

40:30.322 --> 40:32.586
<i>♫ Recalling ♫</i>

40:32.691 --> 40:35.592
<i>[Boy]
Under Section 972/552.</i>

40:35.694 --> 40:38.657
Hello. I wonder
if you could tell me where the—

40:38.697 --> 40:40.665
Piss off!

40:44.870 --> 40:47.896
Hello.

40:48.006 --> 40:49.974
I'll never confess!

40:51.276 --> 40:53.176
[Rattling]

40:53.278 --> 40:55.178
[All Laughing]

40:55.280 --> 40:58.340
Hey, come on!
You gotta interrogate me!

41:08.760 --> 41:10.728
<i>[Man Coughs]</i>

41:24.542 --> 41:26.510
Mrs Buttle?

41:28.813 --> 41:31.611
Uh, Mrs Buttle?

41:39.224 --> 41:42.660
Ah. Um, are you Mrs Buttle?

41:45.430 --> 41:47.398
Um…

41:50.101 --> 41:52.592
my name's Lowry.

41:52.704 --> 41:55.104
Uh, Sam Lowry.

41:57.275 --> 42:00.073
Um, I'm from
the Ministry of Information.

42:02.347 --> 42:05.646
[Clears Throat]
I've come to give you a check.

42:10.755 --> 42:13.053
Um, it's a refund, actually.

42:13.158 --> 42:16.127
–There was a mistake.
–Mistake?

42:16.227 --> 42:18.189
Yes, yes.
Not in my department, of course.

42:18.229 --> 42:20.129
I'm only Records.

42:20.231 --> 42:22.791
No, it, uh—
I'll tell you what it is.

42:22.901 --> 42:27.191
It seems that Mr Buttle was overcharged
by Information Retrieval.

42:27.872 --> 42:30.735
Yes, they don't usually make mistakes,
but, uh…

42:30.775 --> 42:33.175
well, I suppose we're all human.

42:36.414 --> 42:38.314
Oh!

42:38.416 --> 42:40.384
What happened to the, um—

42:44.723 --> 42:48.586
Actually, you know, my coming here
is rather unorthodox, bringing you this check…

42:48.626 --> 42:52.657
as any payments are normally
made through Central Computer, but, um—

42:52.697 --> 42:56.565
Well, as there were
certain… difficulties…

42:56.668 --> 42:59.637
we thought,
well, rather than cause delay…

42:59.738 --> 43:01.968
we'd let you have it now.

43:02.073 --> 43:05.201
You know, it being Christmas and all.

43:05.310 --> 43:07.938
My husband's dead, isn't he?

43:09.881 --> 43:13.845
Um, I do assure you, Mrs Buttle,
the ministry is very scrupulous…

43:13.885 --> 43:16.781
about following up
and eradicating any error.

43:16.821 --> 43:19.718
But if you do have any complaints
you wish to make…

43:19.758 --> 43:23.990
I'd be, well, only too happy
to send you the appropriate forms.

43:24.095 --> 43:26.563
What have you done with his body?

43:29.200 --> 43:32.829
Oh!
[Chuckles] Gosh.

43:32.937 --> 43:35.900
Um, I-I don't know
anything about that, Mrs Buttle.

43:35.940 --> 43:37.902
I'm really just delivering the check.

43:37.942 --> 43:43.676
So, if, um— Look, if you wouldn't mind
just signing these two receipts…

43:43.782 --> 43:48.242
I'd be only too happy to, uh—
to leave you in peace.

43:48.353 --> 43:50.844
[Sobbing]
He hadn't done anything.

43:50.955 --> 43:52.855
He was good!

43:52.957 --> 43:54.857
[Paper Tearing]

43:54.959 --> 43:58.986
What have you done
with his body?

43:59.097 --> 44:01.327
[Sobbing Continues]

44:02.500 --> 44:05.560
[Screaming, Sobbing Continues]

44:05.670 --> 44:08.400
It isn't being very helpful, Mrs Buttle.

44:08.506 --> 44:10.974
[Muffled Screaming]

44:15.146 --> 44:17.609
I didn't have to come here,
you know, Mrs Buttle.

44:17.649 --> 44:20.550
[Boy Shouts]
I'll kill you!

44:20.652 --> 44:22.552
I'll kill you, you bastard!

44:22.654 --> 44:25.623
[Both Shouting]

44:30.995 --> 44:34.055
–Hey!
–[Sobbing Continues]

44:34.165 --> 44:36.258
Get off!

44:36.367 --> 44:38.392
Are you all right?

44:39.771 --> 44:41.739
Are you all right?

44:42.841 --> 44:45.537
<i>[Mrs Buttle Moaning]</i>

44:45.643 --> 44:48.612
<i>Mrs Buttle, are you all right?</i>

44:48.713 --> 44:50.578
It's you!

44:50.682 --> 44:53.651
Wait! Stop! Don't go! Stop!

44:55.720 --> 44:58.018
<i>[Baby Crying In Distance]</i>

45:01.526 --> 45:03.494
[Man Coughs]

45:07.165 --> 45:08.792
Ow!

45:19.644 --> 45:21.771
<i>[Explosion]</i>

45:38.796 --> 45:41.765
<i>[Children Laughing, Chattering]</i>

45:48.006 --> 45:51.900
<i>[Child Laughing]
Oh, look! He'll never get that out!</i>

45:54.112 --> 45:56.979
[Grunts]

45:59.417 --> 46:03.183
[Horn Blasting]

46:05.223 --> 46:08.852
Stop! I had nothing
to do with it! Wait!

46:08.960 --> 46:10.928
Stop!

46:15.233 --> 46:17.997
<i>[Child]
He's coming back!</i>

46:18.102 --> 46:21.560
[Grunting]

46:24.409 --> 46:26.639
[Engine Starts]

46:26.744 --> 46:30.110
<i>–[Children Continue Laughing]
–Jesus Christ!</i>

46:31.249 --> 46:32.944
Jesus—
[Groans]

46:33.051 --> 46:36.282
–Go away.
–Her name's Jill.

46:36.387 --> 46:39.481
What? Jill?

46:39.591 --> 46:42.526
Jill who? Jill who?

46:43.628 --> 46:45.027
Layton.

46:47.298 --> 46:49.698
Jill Layton.

46:49.801 --> 46:53.231
You're a very good little girl.
What are you doing here?

46:53.271 --> 46:55.466
Waiting for my daddy.

46:55.573 --> 46:58.542
He will be pleased
when he gets home.

47:43.121 --> 47:47.319
Sam, I've just
had the Transport Pool onto me.

47:47.425 --> 47:50.688
You don't anything about a personnel transporter
gone missing, do you?

47:50.728 --> 47:53.595
Personnel transporter? What?

47:53.698 --> 47:56.995
<i>–Oh, the prannets. I had
a personal transporter.
–Huh.</i>

47:57.035 --> 47:58.997
I'll do the paperwork in the morning.

47:59.037 --> 48:02.438
Um, is it all right about Mrs Tuttl—

48:02.540 --> 48:05.771
<i>Uh, Buttle's check?</i>

48:05.877 --> 48:07.777
–Uh-huh.
–Can I forget it?

48:07.879 --> 48:09.938
–Yeah.
–Oh, what a relief.

48:10.048 --> 48:12.377
I'm gonna have nightmares, you know.

48:12.417 --> 48:14.612
[Beeping]

48:14.719 --> 48:18.211
–Oh, damn and blast!
–What's the matter?

48:18.323 --> 48:20.223
[Sighs]

48:20.325 --> 48:23.454
I don't suppose you'd happen to know
how I can get round an I RQ/3, do you?

48:23.494 --> 48:26.524
Ooh, all information
on third-level suspects is classified.

48:26.564 --> 48:31.062
All inquiries through Information Retrieval,
and that's hopeless. They
never tell you anything.

48:31.102 --> 48:34.468
Come the time
they want something from us, oh, yes.

48:34.539 --> 48:39.137
There is one way I could get round it.
I could accept my mother's promotion.

48:39.177 --> 48:41.077
Yes.

48:41.179 --> 48:43.238
No!
[Chuckles]

48:43.348 --> 48:45.543
You can't.
You've just turned it down.

48:45.583 --> 48:47.744
I didn't sign the form.

48:48.886 --> 48:50.854
I did it for you.

48:52.090 --> 48:54.820
–You didn't.
–I did.

48:54.926 --> 48:56.484
You didn't!

48:56.594 --> 48:58.755
I did!

48:58.863 --> 49:00.513
What did you do that for?

49:00.598 --> 49:03.624
It's what you wanted, isn't it?
[Echoing]

49:03.735 --> 49:06.499
Oh, I don't know.

49:06.604 --> 49:08.731
I don't know what I want.

49:09.841 --> 49:12.810
Come on,
before they turn the lights out.

49:29.093 --> 49:31.055
<i>[Sam]
There is one way round it.</i>

49:31.095 --> 49:35.319
<i>I could always accept promotion
to Information Retrieval.</i>

50:14.639 --> 50:17.267
Sam!

50:34.192 --> 50:37.025
[Snarling]

50:40.798 --> 50:42.527
[Shouts]

50:54.345 --> 50:56.245
<i>[Bell Dings]</i>

50:56.347 --> 50:58.315
[Groans]

51:27.178 --> 51:30.807
<i>–[Rumbling, Crackling]
–Oh, Christ.</i>

51:34.852 --> 51:37.821
<i>[Hissing, Pumping]</i>

51:45.062 --> 51:48.031
<i>[Rumbling, Gurgling]</i>

51:53.604 --> 51:57.506
What are you doing?
What— My God! What's going on?

51:57.608 --> 52:00.905
<i>–Emergency procedures.
–[Dowser] Emergency procedures!</i>

52:00.945 --> 52:03.311
–I haven't got an emergency!
–Yeah?

52:03.414 --> 52:07.378
–[Sam On Tape] This is an emergency!
–[Woman] Have a nice day.
This has not been a recording.

52:07.418 --> 52:09.318
Aah!

52:09.420 --> 52:12.048
<i>–Here. Sign that.
–[Stammering]</i>

52:13.124 --> 52:15.922
–What is it?
–A 27 B/6.

52:16.027 --> 52:18.256
What do you think it is?
Where's he gone?

52:18.296 --> 52:20.958
<i>Spoor, come here!
Look! I got it! I found it!</i>

52:20.998 --> 52:23.967
Spoor! Spoor!
Come here, Spoor!

52:24.068 --> 52:27.697
It's a bypass valve on this—
on the transformer.

52:27.805 --> 52:30.774
[Dowser Babbling, Indistinct]

52:34.645 --> 52:36.545
–Tuttle!
–[Stammering]

52:36.647 --> 52:38.945
Tuttle. It's Tuttle.

52:40.318 --> 52:42.480
You've had that scab Tuttle here,
ain't ya?

52:42.520 --> 52:45.216
What are you talking about?

52:45.323 --> 52:48.286
–Who fixed your ducts? Huh?
–Fixed your ducts, all right.

52:48.326 --> 52:50.454
I told you before—
they fixed themselves.

52:50.494 --> 52:53.398
Oh, yeah? Then where did this
come from, eh?

52:53.497 --> 52:56.159
Out of your nostril? Eh?

52:56.267 --> 52:58.735
–[Laughing]
–Nostrils, eh? [Laughing]

53:00.304 --> 53:02.272
Central Services.

53:04.609 --> 53:06.571
They don't take kindly to sabotage.

53:06.611 --> 53:10.175
–Sabotage, huh? [Laughing]
–[Spoor Continues Laughing]

53:11.415 --> 53:14.912
<i>–Jesus, this place is in a terrible state.
–[Laughing Continues]</i>

53:14.952 --> 53:17.949
<i>Just a minute!
You're not gonna leave it like this, are you?</i>

53:17.989 --> 53:21.819
Why not? All you gotta do
is blow your nose and it's fixed, innit?

53:21.859 --> 53:23.854
That's right!
[Imitates Nose Blowing]

53:23.894 --> 53:25.862
Well—

53:27.498 --> 53:29.489
Oh, my-

53:29.600 --> 53:31.568
Jesus!

53:41.078 --> 53:43.808
[Shrieking, Snarling]

53:48.986 --> 53:51.955
[Shouting]

54:01.432 --> 54:05.892
<i>[Mrs Buttle]
What have you done with his body?</i>

54:10.675 --> 54:13.269
[Shrieking]

54:22.520 --> 54:24.181
–[Groans]
–[Shrieks]

54:44.475 --> 54:46.443
[Gasps]

55:01.258 --> 55:03.488
[Shouting]

55:34.992 --> 55:38.189
[Shouting Continues]

56:04.722 --> 56:07.714
[Groaning]

56:21.639 --> 56:24.130
[Shouting]

56:35.419 --> 56:37.444
[Shrieking]

57:03.647 --> 57:06.749
<i>–[Doorbell Rings]
–[Whimpering, Gasping]</i>

57:07.585 --> 57:10.053
<i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

57:12.957 --> 57:14.925
<i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

57:16.026 --> 57:17.994
<i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

57:19.396 --> 57:22.229
♫ [Vocalizing]

57:23.334 --> 57:26.730
♫ Mrs Ida Lowry requests
the pleasure of your company ♫

57:26.770 --> 57:28.704
♫At her apartment tonight ♫

57:28.806 --> 57:32.640
♫ From 8:30 ♫

57:32.743 --> 57:34.734
♫To midnight ♫

57:34.845 --> 57:37.075
♫To celebrate the completion ♫

57:37.181 --> 57:40.207
♫ Of her recent cosmetic ♫

57:40.317 --> 57:42.285
<i>♫ Surgery ♫</i>

57:42.386 --> 57:49.986
♫Telegram ♫

57:59.236 --> 58:00.863
Um…

58:01.939 --> 58:03.839
thanks.

58:03.941 --> 58:06.774
–It's reply paid.
–Is it?

58:06.877 --> 58:09.675
Oh. Um—
[Clears Throat]

58:11.148 --> 58:13.048
Two, three—

58:13.150 --> 58:16.113
♫ Mother, I'm sorry, but I'm unable
to come to your party ♫

58:16.153 --> 58:18.849
–You don't have to sing it.
–I don't?

58:18.956 --> 58:20.856
No.

58:20.958 --> 58:23.426
Oh. Sorry.

58:26.563 --> 58:29.860
Aren't you a bit late?
I mean, the party started an hour ago.

58:29.900 --> 58:32.029
Yeah. It's the backlog.
Everybody complains.

58:32.069 --> 58:34.247
–Oh.
–Was it all right otherwise?

58:44.315 --> 58:48.279
[Thinking] Mr Helpmann, I'm keen to
get into Information Retrieval.

58:48.319 --> 58:51.415
Mr Helpmann, I'm dying
to get at this woman. No, no— Ohh!

58:51.455 --> 58:53.423
Oh, God.

58:57.227 --> 59:00.128
–Hold up.
–What? Who are you?

59:00.230 --> 59:03.193
–Hey! What's going on?
–Where's your invitation?

59:03.233 --> 59:06.725
Don't shoot! Don't shoot!
Mother! Mother!

59:06.837 --> 59:08.737
Sam.

59:08.839 --> 59:11.569
I'm so glad you came.

59:11.675 --> 59:14.075
Come in.

59:14.178 --> 59:16.908
–Mother?
–Come in.

59:17.948 --> 59:20.348
Oh, God, Mother, is that you?

59:20.451 --> 59:23.352
Of course.
Isn't it wonderful?

59:23.454 --> 59:26.817
–The bandages came off just this afternoon.
–[Meter Gun Crackling]

59:26.857 --> 59:30.759
Come on, darling. Join in the fun.
Simply everybody's here.

59:30.861 --> 59:32.823
–Is Mr Helpmann here?
–[Meter Gun Squealing]

59:32.863 --> 59:34.825
–Would you stop shoving—
–Yes, he is.

59:34.865 --> 59:37.828
Mr Helpmann is here,
and he wants to talk to you.

59:37.868 --> 59:40.098
Good. I want to talk to him.

59:40.204 --> 59:44.335
He says that you're the first person
ever to refuse a promotion.

59:44.375 --> 59:46.837
–Ah, well—
–He thinks you should see a doctor.

59:46.877 --> 59:50.774
–Actually, Mother, I've decided—
–Oh, Louis! Louis, you know Sam.

59:50.814 --> 59:53.214
Can you believe it?

59:53.317 --> 59:56.115
It's just me and my little knife.

59:56.220 --> 59:59.183
–Snip, snip, slice, slice.
–[Woman] It's marvelous.

59:59.223 --> 01:00:02.124
–Can you believe it?
–Congratulations.

01:00:02.226 --> 01:00:04.989
–But this is just the beginning.
–Oh, really?

01:00:05.029 --> 01:00:08.092
Oh, Christ, yes.
You've seen her with her clothes off.

01:00:08.132 --> 01:00:11.329
Faces are a doddle
compared to tits and ass.

01:00:11.435 --> 01:00:14.404
–No hairline.
–Oh, really, Louis!

01:00:15.873 --> 01:00:18.645
I've been looking for you
everywhere, Ida.

01:00:19.610 --> 01:00:22.773
[Ida Chuckles]

01:00:22.880 --> 01:00:25.843
Mother. Mother, I have to
talk to Mr Helpmann.

01:00:25.883 --> 01:00:29.512
–Oh, you stupid sod.
–Dear boy.

01:00:29.620 --> 01:00:31.949
What do you think of your mother now?

01:00:31.989 --> 01:00:33.969
<i>[Man]
It'll never last.</i>

01:00:36.293 --> 01:00:38.193
Excuse me.

01:00:38.295 --> 01:00:40.820
Dr Chapman,
did you say something?

01:00:40.931 --> 01:00:42.911
That technique— I've tried it.

01:00:43.000 --> 01:00:46.401
Oh, nice effect,
but highly unstable.

01:00:46.503 --> 01:00:50.701
<i>In six months
she'll look like Grandma Moses.</i>

01:00:50.808 --> 01:00:55.773
Now, see here, Chapman, at least mine
don't end up looking like they've been mugged.

01:00:55.813 --> 01:00:58.407
Sam! Sam!

01:01:00.517 --> 01:01:05.386
<i>[Mrs Buttle]
What have you done with his body?</i>

01:01:05.489 --> 01:01:08.185
Sam!

01:01:08.292 --> 01:01:09.691
<i>Sam?</i>

01:01:09.793 --> 01:01:13.757
–What on earth's happened to you?
–There was a little complication.

01:01:13.797 --> 01:01:18.996
Dr Chapman says it often happens
with a delicate skin like mine.

01:01:19.103 --> 01:01:21.003
Nothing to worry about.

01:01:21.105 --> 01:01:24.635
He's promised me these bandages
will be off in a jiffy.

01:01:24.675 --> 01:01:27.571
–Actually, there's someone I want to meet.
–Oh, I know.

01:01:27.611 --> 01:01:29.909
[Whispers]
I know.

01:01:32.216 --> 01:01:34.684
There we are.

01:01:34.785 --> 01:01:38.516
I'm going to leave
you two lovebirds in peace.

01:01:39.990 --> 01:01:41.890
[Exhales]
Hello, Shirley.

01:01:41.992 --> 01:01:45.484
–[Gasps] Oh, God.
–Come on!

01:01:45.596 --> 01:01:47.564
Do you want a drink?

01:01:50.300 --> 01:01:52.632
[Ida]
Oh. Hello. [Giggles]

01:01:52.736 --> 01:01:55.637
–[Sighs]
–[Ida] Chase those years away!

01:01:55.739 --> 01:01:58.105
Listen, Shirley…

01:01:58.208 --> 01:02:02.366
your mother and my mother,
they seem to have got the idea that—

01:02:02.379 --> 01:02:04.842
Look, I'm very flattered
and, uh, well…

01:02:04.882 --> 01:02:07.845
I just don't want you to be
under any false impressions.

01:02:07.885 --> 01:02:09.785
It's all right.

01:02:09.887 --> 01:02:12.185
I don't like you either.

01:02:13.757 --> 01:02:15.725
<i>[Jack]
Sam!</i>

01:02:16.560 --> 01:02:18.922
Jack. [Chuckling]
Excuse me, Shirley.

01:02:18.962 --> 01:02:22.659
–[Shirley Groans]
–I'm s— I'm sorry.

01:02:23.700 --> 01:02:27.067
<i>–Sam! You remember Alison?
–[Woman] Evening.</i>

01:02:27.171 --> 01:02:29.867
Alison. Sam Lowry.
Old friend.

01:02:29.973 --> 01:02:32.203
Alison, yes, of course.

01:02:32.309 --> 01:02:35.272
–You look different.
–Well, I'm two years older.

01:02:35.312 --> 01:02:37.490
–And she's been to Dr Jaffe.
–Ah.

01:02:37.548 --> 01:02:40.644
She doesn't like me telling people,
but, in fact, she's really pleased.

01:02:40.684 --> 01:02:44.481
–I knew there was something different.
–Remember how they used to stick out?

01:02:44.521 --> 01:02:48.582
What? Oh, yes.
Uh, well, rather.

01:02:48.692 --> 01:02:52.454
–Always used to wonder if they were real.
–What, my ears?

01:02:53.363 --> 01:02:55.263
Sorry?

01:02:55.365 --> 01:02:57.492
Dr Jaffe pinned her ears back.

01:02:57.601 --> 01:02:59.563
[Chuckling]
Yes, that's what I—

01:02:59.603 --> 01:03:01.932
Always used to wonder
if she wore falsies.

01:03:01.972 --> 01:03:04.236
Ah! Mr Helpmann.

01:03:04.341 --> 01:03:07.208
False ears—
Mr Helpmann!

01:03:07.377 --> 01:03:10.007
–Hello, Jack.
–You remember my wife, Alison?

01:03:10.047 --> 01:03:12.009
Yes, of course.
Barbara, isn't it?

01:03:12.049 --> 01:03:13.963
–How are you?
–Well, actuall—

01:03:14.051 --> 01:03:17.014
Barbara's very well, thank you, sir.
Very well indeed. How are you?

01:03:17.054 --> 01:03:18.954
–Fine, thanks.
–Good.

01:03:19.056 --> 01:03:22.653
Hello, Sam. Ida said you might be here.
Have you got a minute?

01:03:22.693 --> 01:03:25.594
–Would you excuse us?
–Oh, no, of course.

01:03:25.696 --> 01:03:28.324
Of course.
Come on, Alison— Barbara.

01:03:29.800 --> 01:03:31.768
Sam.

01:03:34.938 --> 01:03:36.906
I need your help.

01:03:39.443 --> 01:03:41.741
[Grunting]

01:03:43.747 --> 01:03:46.375
[Flushes]

01:03:58.862 --> 01:04:01.422
[Exhales]
Thanks very much, Sam.

01:04:01.531 --> 01:04:04.159
Mr Helpmann,
I'm glad to be of help.

01:04:04.268 --> 01:04:07.829
–If I can help you—
–Ah, well, actually-

01:04:07.938 --> 01:04:09.929
Oh.

01:04:12.509 --> 01:04:15.410
Your father and I were very close.

01:04:15.512 --> 01:04:19.846
Of course, Jeremiah was senior to me,
but we were close friends.

01:04:19.950 --> 01:04:22.384
Especially after the bombing.

01:04:23.553 --> 01:04:27.319
And I keep his name alive
at the office every day.

01:04:28.358 --> 01:04:31.088
It's as though he's there
still speaking to me.

01:04:31.128 --> 01:04:34.529
“'Ere I am.

01:04:34.631 --> 01:04:37.225
J.H.”

01:04:38.869 --> 01:04:40.996
The ghost in the machine.

01:04:43.373 --> 01:04:46.831
I know he would have
wanted me to help you.

01:04:48.879 --> 01:04:51.279
And I promised your mother…

01:04:51.381 --> 01:04:55.784
that I'd take you on to the team
at Information Retrieval.

01:04:55.886 --> 01:04:58.218
But I gather that, um—

01:04:58.322 --> 01:05:03.055
Well, actually, Mr Helpmann, I've, uh—
I've changed my mind.

01:05:03.160 --> 01:05:06.459
I've decided I'd accept the transfer…

01:05:06.563 --> 01:05:08.531
if I'm not too late.

01:05:09.566 --> 01:05:11.466
Too late?

01:05:11.568 --> 01:05:13.627
That's for me to say.

01:05:13.737 --> 01:05:16.205
Well -Well, then, I, uh—

01:05:19.076 --> 01:05:21.544
Welcome to Information Retrieval.

01:05:55.112 --> 01:05:57.080
Uh, my name's Lowry.

01:05:58.248 --> 01:06:00.239
Sam Lowry.

01:06:00.350 --> 01:06:03.751
I've been told to report
to Mr Warrenn.

01:06:03.854 --> 01:06:05.981
<i>Thirtieth floor, sir.</i>

01:06:06.089 --> 01:06:08.057
<i>You're expected.</i>

01:06:09.726 --> 01:06:13.628
Um, don't you want to search me?

01:06:13.730 --> 01:06:15.698
<i>No, sir.</i>

01:06:16.967 --> 01:06:19.739
<i>–Want to see my I.D?
–No need, sir.</i>

01:06:21.805 --> 01:06:25.102
<i>–But I could be anybody.
–No, you couldn't, sir.</i>

01:06:25.142 --> 01:06:28.043
<i>This is Information Retrieval.</i>

01:06:28.145 --> 01:06:31.775
<i>–[Elevator Bell Dings]
–The lift's arrived, sir.</i>

01:07:35.579 --> 01:07:38.548
<i>[Men Shouting, Clamoring]</i>

01:07:53.663 --> 01:07:57.755
–[Men Shouting, Clamoring]
–[Man] I want that order rescinded!

01:08:18.555 --> 01:08:20.649
<i>–Half as terrorists, the rest as victims.
–[Clamoring Continues]</i>

01:08:20.689 --> 01:08:22.350
Yes. No.

01:08:22.459 --> 01:08:24.188
Definitely no!

01:08:24.294 --> 01:08:27.057
–My name's Lowry, Mr Warrenn. Sam Lowry.
–Ah, Lowry!

01:08:27.096 --> 01:08:31.591
–[Shouting, Clamoring Continue]
–Yes. No. Cancel that. Okay.

01:08:31.701 --> 01:08:34.197
–Glad to have you aboard. Yes.
–These requisitions—

01:08:34.237 --> 01:08:37.334
–Sir, I'd like to point this out—
–No! Don't be ridiculous, Jenkins.

01:08:37.374 --> 01:08:39.881
–About these invoices—
–Yes. Yes. Yes.

01:08:39.975 --> 01:08:42.205
You'll like it up here.
Send that back.

01:08:42.245 --> 01:08:45.475
We've got a crack team of-
Are they kidding? Decision makers.

01:08:45.515 --> 01:08:47.415
No, in triplicate.

01:08:47.517 --> 01:08:50.046
I'm expecting big things—
Two copies to Financial!

01:08:50.086 --> 01:08:53.988
No. No.
Don't let Progress see those.

01:08:54.090 --> 01:08:57.754
Between you and me, Lowry, this— No, no!
department— Tell Records to get stuffed!

01:08:57.794 --> 01:08:59.694
is about to be upgraded and—

01:08:59.796 --> 01:09:03.562
Ah! Here we are.

01:09:03.667 --> 01:09:06.966
<i>Your very own number
on your very own door.</i>

01:09:07.002 --> 01:09:09.904
And behind that door,
your very own office.

01:09:10.006 --> 01:09:12.907
Congratulations, DZ/015.

01:09:13.009 --> 01:09:15.033
Welcome to the team.

01:09:15.145 --> 01:09:17.511
Yes! No! Cancel that!

01:09:17.613 --> 01:09:19.990
<i>Send two copies to Financial!</i>

01:10:31.121 --> 01:10:33.589
[Grunting]

01:10:36.693 --> 01:10:38.991
[Grunting Continues]

01:10:53.877 --> 01:10:55.839
Well, you can't borrow any more chairs!

01:10:55.879 --> 01:10:58.508
There's only one left in here now,
and I need that to sit on!

01:10:58.548 --> 01:11:00.140
What?

01:11:00.250 --> 01:11:02.275
Oh.

01:11:02.385 --> 01:11:04.945
Sorry.

01:11:05.055 --> 01:11:07.114
Who are you?

01:11:07.223 --> 01:11:09.623
My name's Lowry.
Sam Lowry.

01:11:09.726 --> 01:11:13.025
Oh, yes.
The new boy from next door.

01:11:14.064 --> 01:11:16.965
My name's Lime.
Harvey Lime.

01:11:17.067 --> 01:11:18.967
Welcome to Expediting.

01:11:19.069 --> 01:11:22.032
I say, look, would you mind
if I borrowed your computer console?

01:11:22.072 --> 01:11:25.035
–What?
–Yes, I'll let you have it back in 10 minutes.

01:11:25.075 --> 01:11:28.670
You want to take my console
into your office?

01:11:28.778 --> 01:11:30.678
Yes. Just for a few minutes.

01:11:30.780 --> 01:11:32.805
I-I'll tell you what.

01:11:32.916 --> 01:11:34.907
You tell me what you want…

01:11:35.018 --> 01:11:37.179
and I'll do it for you.

01:11:37.287 --> 01:11:39.585
I'm a bit of a whiz on that thing.

01:11:39.689 --> 01:11:41.589
Um…

01:11:41.691 --> 01:11:43.591
all right.

01:11:43.693 --> 01:11:47.527
Uh, I need some information
on a woman named Layton.

01:11:47.630 --> 01:11:49.598
A woman, eh?

01:11:49.699 --> 01:11:51.997
–I see.
–Yes.

01:11:52.102 --> 01:11:55.799
I know her age and distinguishing marks,
but I need an address or a place of work.

01:11:55.839 --> 01:11:58.740
This your dream girl, is it?

01:11:58.842 --> 01:12:01.003
What? Um—

01:12:01.111 --> 01:12:03.170
Look, let me use your console.

01:12:03.279 --> 01:12:05.179
You must be joking.

01:12:05.281 --> 01:12:10.275
[Chuckles] When there's a woman involved,
there's no stopping me.

01:12:10.386 --> 01:12:12.354
Let's have that sheet.

01:12:14.257 --> 01:12:16.225
[Blows]

01:12:21.331 --> 01:12:23.299
Sod it! It's broken!

01:12:23.399 --> 01:12:25.367
You haven't switched it on.

01:12:26.636 --> 01:12:28.604
Oh, yes.

01:12:32.175 --> 01:12:34.137
Look, you're putting me off standing there.

01:12:34.177 --> 01:12:38.274
–Why don't you go back to your office
and I'll give you a knock when I'm finished.
–Um—

01:12:38.314 --> 01:12:40.888
Go on. I'm not going to elope with her.

01:12:42.152 --> 01:12:44.120
All right.

01:12:51.161 --> 01:12:54.494
[Beeping]

01:13:05.842 --> 01:13:08.402
[Beeping Continues]

01:13:19.222 --> 01:13:21.952
Sam!

01:13:43.746 --> 01:13:46.340
Sam.

01:13:48.084 --> 01:13:50.052
Don't go.

01:13:51.654 --> 01:13:54.179
Please.

01:13:55.291 --> 01:13:57.316
<i>[Knocking]</i>

01:14:01.097 --> 01:14:03.065
<i>[Knocking Continues]</i>

01:14:05.835 --> 01:14:07.996
Well?

01:14:08.104 --> 01:14:10.504
Computers are my forte.

01:14:10.607 --> 01:14:12.507
Let me see.

01:14:12.609 --> 01:14:16.773
“Jillian Layton. Coloring: white.
Hair: blonde. Eyes: blue. Height: 5 foot 4.

01:14:16.813 --> 01:14:19.475
Distinguishing marks:
scar on left”—

01:14:19.582 --> 01:14:21.482
Is this all you've got?

01:14:21.584 --> 01:14:25.486
Best to take things slowly
where some women are concerned.

01:14:25.588 --> 01:14:27.556
–Let me see.
–[Groans]

01:14:27.657 --> 01:14:30.592
–[Beeping]
–Hey! That's mine!

01:14:31.628 --> 01:14:33.528
“Layton.

01:14:33.630 --> 01:14:35.530
“Truck driver.

01:14:35.632 --> 01:14:40.228
All inquiries, reference office
of 412/L, room 5001.”

01:14:43.773 --> 01:14:45.902
Ah, Lowry, glad I caught you.
No! Send that back!

01:14:45.942 --> 01:14:48.538
<i>–Mr Warrenn!
–Are you settling down?
I want this order rescinded.</i>

01:14:48.578 --> 01:14:51.040
There's a query about a personnel transporter
you took out from the pool.

01:14:51.080 --> 01:14:52.980
Tell them no.
Tell them yes.

01:14:53.082 --> 01:14:55.712
Or was it a personnel carrier
you took out from Transportation?

01:14:55.752 --> 01:14:58.715
Send that up to Security.
Anyway, tidy it up, Lowry.

01:14:58.755 --> 01:15:00.717
There's a good chap.
And get a new suit.

01:15:00.757 --> 01:15:02.719
<i>–[Elevator Bell Dings]
–Don't you want the lift?</i>

01:15:02.759 --> 01:15:05.227
[Men Clamoring]

01:15:10.199 --> 01:15:13.396
<i>[Elevator Bell Dings]</i>

01:15:25.214 --> 01:15:27.682
[Static, Frequencies Tuning]

01:15:46.202 --> 01:15:49.262
[Buzzes]

01:15:59.983 --> 01:16:02.975
<i>–[Sam Clears Throat]
–[Mouthing Words]</i>

01:16:19.969 --> 01:16:23.302
–[Headset: Man Screaming]
–Can I help you?

01:16:23.406 --> 01:16:26.898
<i>[Whimpering, Gasping]
No! No! No! Please!</i>

01:16:27.010 --> 01:16:30.907
<i>–[Screaming, Pleading Continue]
–I'm, uh— I'm looking for Officer 412/L.</i>

01:16:30.947 --> 01:16:33.415
He won't be very long now.

01:16:34.450 --> 01:16:37.977
<i>–[Alarm Ringing]
–Hmm. I thought so.</i>

01:16:38.087 --> 01:16:40.055
<i>[Buzzer Buzzes]</i>

01:16:44.927 --> 01:16:47.555
You may go in now.

01:16:50.099 --> 01:16:53.193
Oh, uh, not that one.

01:16:53.302 --> 01:16:56.169
<i>That one. Yes.</i>

01:16:56.272 --> 01:16:59.241
<i>[Whirring]</i>

01:17:03.946 --> 01:17:06.881
Excuse me.
Are you Officer 412/L?

01:17:07.917 --> 01:17:10.385
–[Whirring Continues]
–[Groaning]

01:17:13.289 --> 01:17:15.257
Excuse me!

01:17:16.592 --> 01:17:18.287
Jack.

01:17:18.394 --> 01:17:20.385
Sam.

01:17:20.496 --> 01:17:23.326
–Ah! I heard you were coming aboard.
–[Whirring Stops]

01:17:23.366 --> 01:17:27.393
Congratulations, “DZ/015.”

01:17:27.503 --> 01:17:29.528
Thanks.
Are you Officer 412/L?

01:17:29.639 --> 01:17:32.039
Uh-huh. That's me.

01:17:32.141 --> 01:17:35.440
Oh, and, Sam,
a very happy Christmas.

01:17:35.545 --> 01:17:37.507
–Thanks, Jack.
–Are you settling in all right?

01:17:37.547 --> 01:17:40.880
Yes, fine. Jack, I—
I need some information.

01:17:40.983 --> 01:17:44.113
Oh, Sam, this is Information Retrieval,
not Information Dispersal.

01:17:44.153 --> 01:17:46.053
–[Chuckles]
–Hey! Amy!

01:17:46.155 --> 01:17:48.117
Don't throw the ball around in here.

01:17:48.157 --> 01:17:50.057
I'm not Amy. I'm Holly.

01:17:50.159 --> 01:17:52.255
Did I call you Amy, darling?
I'm sorry.

01:17:52.295 --> 01:17:54.290
–A triplet?
–One of them, I think.

01:17:54.330 --> 01:17:57.260
Barbara's taken the other two
Christmas shopping.

01:17:57.300 --> 01:18:00.263
You're not going to keep
calling her Barbara, are you?

01:18:00.303 --> 01:18:03.066
Why ever not?
Barbara's a perfectly good name, isn't it?

01:18:03.106 --> 01:18:05.631
Don't you like it?

01:18:05.741 --> 01:18:07.834
Yes, it's… fine.

01:18:07.944 --> 01:18:10.913
Come on.
Let's get these together.

01:18:11.013 --> 01:18:13.776
<i>–Jack.
–Now bring me the blue one over there.</i>

01:18:13.816 --> 01:18:15.778
I need to find out about a woman.

01:18:15.818 --> 01:18:19.916
Come on, Chloe, let's show Uncle Sam here
how we can make the word “cat.” Shall we?

01:18:19.956 --> 01:18:22.516
–I'm Holly.
–Sorry, love. So you are.

01:18:22.625 --> 01:18:24.593
–Cat.
–This is her.

01:18:25.862 --> 01:18:27.762
Layton.

01:18:27.864 --> 01:18:29.832
Oh, shit.

01:18:31.367 --> 01:18:33.596
–How much do you know about this?
–Uh, not much.

01:18:33.636 --> 01:18:36.070
What does B58/732 mean to you?

01:18:36.172 --> 01:18:39.073
–Buttle.
–I knew it.

01:18:39.175 --> 01:18:42.338
You always were bloody quick, Sam.

01:18:42.445 --> 01:18:45.812
Who else knows?
Warrenn? Helpmann?

01:18:45.915 --> 01:18:48.211
I don't know.
I only know you got the wrong man.

01:18:48.251 --> 01:18:51.214
[Scoffs]
Information Transit got the wrong man.

01:18:51.254 --> 01:18:53.154
<i>I got the right man.</i>

01:18:53.256 --> 01:18:55.718
The wrong man was delivered to me
as the right man.

01:18:55.758 --> 01:18:59.222
I accepted him on good faith
as the right man. Was I wrong?

01:18:59.262 --> 01:19:01.162
You killed Buttle?

01:19:02.265 --> 01:19:06.896
Sam, there are very rigid parameters laid down
to prevent such things happening.

01:19:06.936 --> 01:19:10.366
It wasn't my fault that Buttle's heart condition
didn't appear on Tuttle's file.

01:19:10.406 --> 01:19:12.368
Come and look.
How you getting on?

01:19:12.408 --> 01:19:15.377
<i>–Jack.
–A, B, C—</i>

01:19:15.478 --> 01:19:17.773
–I really need to know about—
–Tuttle?

01:19:17.813 --> 01:19:20.543
Well, we're gonna have to bring
Mr Tuttle in, aren't we?

01:19:20.583 --> 01:19:23.546
And interrogate him
at the same voltage as Mr Buttle.

01:19:23.586 --> 01:19:25.548
And juggle the books
in Electrical Banking.

01:19:25.588 --> 01:19:29.752
–What has Tuttle done?
–We suspect him of, uh, freelance subversion.

01:19:29.792 --> 01:19:31.760
A freelance subversive.

01:19:31.861 --> 01:19:34.857
Then all I need to wrap up the case
is the Layton woman.

01:19:34.897 --> 01:19:36.797
What has she done?

01:19:36.899 --> 01:19:39.729
Well, she witnessed the Tuttle—
Um, the Buttle arrest.

01:19:39.769 --> 01:19:42.198
Since then, she's been going around
making wild allegations…

01:19:42.238 --> 01:19:44.734
obviously trying to exploit the situation.

01:19:44.774 --> 01:19:47.103
She's working for someone,
and I don't think it's us.

01:19:47.143 --> 01:19:49.906
<i>–That's it. Over there, love.
–[Whispers] Terrorist?</i>

01:19:49.946 --> 01:19:52.176
<i>[Buzzing]</i>

01:19:52.281 --> 01:19:54.577
[Receptionist]
Mr Lint, the next customer has been delivered.

01:19:54.617 --> 01:19:57.847
–Thank you, Myrtle.
–What are you gonna do
about the Layton woman?

01:19:57.887 --> 01:20:03.085
Well, I put her on the detention list.
Security should have her here before 6:00.

01:20:03.125 --> 01:20:06.956
<i>What, here? So that she can
spill the beans inside the department?</i>

01:20:06.996 --> 01:20:09.058
<i>–[Toys Clattering]
–Don't do that!</i>

01:20:09.098 --> 01:20:12.465
Jack, why don't I
try and get to her for you?

01:20:12.568 --> 01:20:15.537
I'll, um— I'll deactivate her.

01:20:15.638 --> 01:20:19.302
What does that mean, Sam? I don't want
to get involved in anything unsavory.

01:20:19.342 --> 01:20:20.969
Trust me, Jack.

01:20:22.511 --> 01:20:27.577
–Come on, darling. Put these away now.
Mummy'll be here soon.
–Let me have her file.

01:20:27.617 --> 01:20:30.085
[Chuckles]
Look, trust me, Jack.

01:20:31.454 --> 01:20:34.321
All right.
Come on here.

01:20:34.423 --> 01:20:38.416
All right, but for Christ's sake,
don't lose it.

01:20:38.527 --> 01:20:41.052
All right.

01:20:41.163 --> 01:20:43.426
<i>You sit down there, Mary.
Sam.</i>

01:20:43.466 --> 01:20:45.434
Don't worry.
I'll get to her.

01:20:45.534 --> 01:20:48.570
You'll never get anywhere
in a suit like that.

01:20:49.605 --> 01:20:51.300
Here.

01:20:52.341 --> 01:20:54.571
Try this.

01:20:54.677 --> 01:20:57.077
–Bye-bye.
–Bye!

01:20:57.179 --> 01:21:01.445
Uh, but, Jack, I—

01:21:01.550 --> 01:21:05.714
Put it on, big boy.
I won't look at your willy.

01:21:11.327 --> 01:21:14.296
<i>[Rattling]</i>

01:21:14.397 --> 01:21:16.892
<i>–[Elevator Bell Dings]
–[Grunting]</i>

01:21:16.932 --> 01:21:19.423
[Officer]
Oh, let him go.

01:21:21.937 --> 01:21:25.065
–[Grunting]
–[Dinging, Buzzing]

01:21:27.543 --> 01:21:30.573
<i>–[Guard] Trier, isn't he?
–[Dinging, Buzzing Continue]</i>

01:21:30.613 --> 01:21:34.174
<i>–[Beeps]
–[Jingling]</i>

01:21:37.386 --> 01:21:39.286
<i>[Buzzer Buzzes]</i>

01:21:39.388 --> 01:21:42.016
–[Beeping]
–[Snapping, Crackling]

01:21:43.726 --> 01:21:46.456
<i>[Buzzer Buzzes]</i>

01:21:46.562 --> 01:21:48.757
<i>[Loud Squeak]</i>

01:21:55.504 --> 01:21:57.665
[Beeping]

01:21:57.773 --> 01:21:59.297
[Buzzer Buzzes]

01:22:04.747 --> 01:22:09.377
Just— I've been to
the department of—

