Uh, we can't allow that, sir.
It's more than our job's worth.

01:42:24.732 --> 01:42:27.633
Jill!
Jill, you must be here! Jill!

01:42:27.735 --> 01:42:31.132
Look, sir, you can fill in an application form,
sir, if you're a relative.

01:42:31.172 --> 01:42:33.072
Now, do stop, sir. Please.

01:42:33.174 --> 01:42:35.404
[Groans]
Jill? Jill?

01:42:35.510 --> 01:42:37.424
Oh, dear, oh, dear, oh, dear.

01:42:37.512 --> 01:42:39.639
[Groans]

01:42:41.049 --> 01:42:44.678
Sorry about that, sir.
Regulations.

01:42:44.786 --> 01:42:47.755
[Siren Wailing]

01:42:50.458 --> 01:42:53.388
<i>[Warrenn] This is a black eye
for the department, Lowry.</i>

01:42:53.428 --> 01:42:55.723
I don't care how you behaved
when you were at Records.

01:42:55.763 --> 01:42:58.560
Information Retrieval
is an executive branch.

01:42:58.600 --> 01:43:01.462
We're proud of our reputation
and we protect it.

01:43:01.502 --> 01:43:05.466
Damn it, Lowry! That convoy of personnel
carriers is still not accounted for!

01:43:05.506 --> 01:43:08.503
I thought I told you to deal with it.
And what the hell is this mess?

01:43:08.543 --> 01:43:10.738
An empty desk is an efficient desk.

01:43:10.778 --> 01:43:13.542
Good God.
Queries from Security.

01:43:13.648 --> 01:43:15.877
Searches from Central Banking
about a check?

01:43:15.917 --> 01:43:18.846
Clarification notices from Accounting
concerning unreturned receipts?

01:43:18.886 --> 01:43:22.378
–Mr Warrenn, I have to find out about—
–Get up!

01:43:22.490 --> 01:43:25.857
I don't know what's going on here, Lowry.

01:43:25.960 --> 01:43:31.192
But don't think you can intimidate us
with your friends and relatives in high places.

01:43:31.232 --> 01:43:34.395
–Now shape up!
–[Men Clamoring]

01:43:36.871 --> 01:43:39.772
Lime, I have to use your computer.

01:43:39.874 --> 01:43:42.274
Sorry.
A bit busy at the moment.

01:43:42.377 --> 01:43:45.941
You seem to have rather a lot
to get on with yourself.

01:43:50.885 --> 01:43:54.048
<i>–[Grunting, Chuckling]
–Shit.</i>

01:43:55.390 --> 01:43:57.290
Come off it, Jack.

01:43:57.392 --> 01:44:00.355
Of course you can check
to see if she's been arrested.

01:44:00.395 --> 01:44:05.360
I'm sorry, Sam. I'm afraid this case has become
much more complicated since last we… talked.

01:44:05.400 --> 01:44:08.529
But she's innocent, Jack.
She's done nothing wrong.

01:44:08.569 --> 01:44:11.532
Tell that to the wives of the security men
she blew up this afternoon.

01:44:11.572 --> 01:44:14.146
–[Groans]
–She's not alone in all this.

01:44:14.242 --> 01:44:17.372
We've just had a report in that Tuttle
has wrecked an entire flat…

01:44:17.412 --> 01:44:19.874
and sabotaged
adjacent Central Services.

01:44:19.914 --> 01:44:22.877
As a matter of fact,
it looks like on your block.

01:44:22.917 --> 01:44:26.283
I should keep my eyes open
if I were you, Sam. Bye.

01:44:27.255 --> 01:44:30.485
But, Jack, you don't really think Tuttle
and the girl are in league, do you?

01:44:30.525 --> 01:44:31.924
I do.

01:44:32.026 --> 01:44:34.188
Everything's connected
all along the line.

01:44:34.228 --> 01:44:36.624
Cause and effect.
That's the beauty of it.

01:44:36.664 --> 01:44:40.426
Our job is to trace the connections
and, uh, reveal them.

01:44:42.070 --> 01:44:45.033
This whole Buttle-Tuttle confusion
was obviously planned from the inside.

01:44:45.073 --> 01:44:46.973
Bye-bye.

01:44:47.075 --> 01:44:49.305
Oh, but, Jack!

01:44:49.410 --> 01:44:51.970
She's innocent, Jack.

01:44:52.080 --> 01:44:54.981
Sam, we've always been close,
haven't we?

01:44:55.083 --> 01:44:56.983
Yes, Jack?

01:44:57.085 --> 01:45:00.715
Well, until this all blows over
just stay away from me.

01:45:01.656 --> 01:45:03.624
But—

01:45:48.903 --> 01:45:51.167
[Laughing]

01:45:55.243 --> 01:45:57.211
<i>[Lime Screaming]</i>

01:46:02.984 --> 01:46:05.452
<i>[Explosion]</i>

01:47:05.880 --> 01:47:07.905
Oh, my God.

01:47:10.585 --> 01:47:12.143
<i>[Sam]
You.</i>

01:47:13.387 --> 01:47:16.322
It's you.
What's happening?

01:47:16.424 --> 01:47:18.517
What's happening?

01:47:18.626 --> 01:47:20.588
Your thermostat's gone,
and then some.

01:47:20.628 --> 01:47:22.590
–And then some!
–[Phone Buzzing]

01:47:22.630 --> 01:47:24.530
What's happened to my flat?

01:47:24.632 --> 01:47:28.090
Hello? What?
It's for you.

01:47:28.202 --> 01:47:31.199
<i>–But as you don't live here anymore-
–What?</i>

01:47:31.239 --> 01:47:35.005
Absolutely.
Do you know what this is?

01:47:35.109 --> 01:47:37.236
This is an H2206…

01:47:37.345 --> 01:47:41.839
authorizing the compulsory,
temporary requisitioning of this flat…

01:47:41.949 --> 01:47:43.911
<i>for our necessary repairs.</i>

01:47:43.951 --> 01:47:45.851
–Repairs!
–What?

01:47:45.953 --> 01:47:48.416
–No! You—[Grunting]
–Don't forget your receipt.

01:47:48.456 --> 01:47:51.552
–Oh! Oh! Oh!
–No, sir. Don't forget your receipt.

01:47:51.592 --> 01:47:54.722
I'm sorry, but I'm a bit
of a stickler for paperwork.

01:47:54.762 --> 01:47:57.725
<i>[Dowser]
He's a stickler for paperwork, sir!</i>

01:47:57.765 --> 01:48:00.359
<i>–[Dowser Laughs]
–Bastards!</i>

01:48:02.803 --> 01:48:04.862
<i>[Man]
Shh.</i>

01:48:10.845 --> 01:48:13.211
Tuttle.

01:48:13.314 --> 01:48:15.714
–What are you doing?
–Shh.

01:48:30.031 --> 01:48:32.397
<i>[Sam Groaning]</i>

01:48:32.500 --> 01:48:34.491
<i>Phew-ee.</i>

01:48:50.718 --> 01:48:52.686
[Gurgling]

01:49:02.396 --> 01:49:05.854
[Spoor, Dowser Muttering]

01:49:05.967 --> 01:49:08.401
Oh, God.

01:49:08.502 --> 01:49:10.970
–Jesus Christ!
–The smell! Stop!

01:49:12.807 --> 01:49:14.707
Filling up with—

01:49:14.809 --> 01:49:18.643
<i>–[Gurgling Continues]
–Oh, God.</i>

01:49:20.081 --> 01:49:22.572
Oh, Jesus!

01:49:22.683 --> 01:49:25.550
[Both Screaming]

01:49:25.653 --> 01:49:28.383
Oh!
[Groans]

01:49:31.092 --> 01:49:33.060
[Laughs]
Shit!

01:49:34.729 --> 01:49:36.709
We're all in it together, kid.

01:49:36.731 --> 01:49:38.699
[Sam Laughing]

01:49:48.943 --> 01:49:51.503
<i>[Sam]
Jill. Jill!</i>

01:49:52.546 --> 01:49:55.913
Jill. Oh, God.

01:49:56.017 --> 01:49:59.509
Are you all right?
What happened to you after-

01:49:59.620 --> 01:50:02.453
Your face. Are you hurt?

01:50:03.491 --> 01:50:05.391
Um, no, I-I'm fine.

01:50:05.493 --> 01:50:08.929
It's -Well—

01:50:09.030 --> 01:50:11.555
I've been worried sick about you.

01:50:16.804 --> 01:50:19.967
<i>[Clears Throat]</i>

01:50:25.446 --> 01:50:28.350
–Who was that?
–That's a friend of mine. He—

01:50:28.449 --> 01:50:31.646
<i>–[Sirens Wailing]
–Oh, God. Holy shit.</i>

01:50:31.752 --> 01:50:35.779
We'd better get out of here quick.
Come on. Quietly.

01:50:39.794 --> 01:50:41.906
[Sam]
Look out. Here. Take this.

01:50:44.131 --> 01:50:46.099
Looks big.

01:50:56.710 --> 01:50:58.678
Here.

01:51:00.414 --> 01:51:02.712
Quick. Quick.

01:51:37.685 --> 01:51:41.143
–Are you sure this is all right?
–Yes. Yes, certain.

01:51:42.590 --> 01:51:44.717
My mother's away for Christmas.

01:51:46.093 --> 01:51:48.931
She's spending it at the plastic surgeon's.

01:51:51.999 --> 01:51:54.126
The wraps come off tomorrow.

01:52:34.575 --> 01:52:38.978
Lock the door after me.
Don't answer the phone to anyone.

01:52:39.079 --> 01:52:41.343
I won't be long.

01:52:42.583 --> 01:52:45.546
–Where are you going?
–I know a way to save you.

01:52:45.586 --> 01:52:48.816
–Trust me. I can do it.
–But you can't go without me.

01:52:48.856 --> 01:52:50.824
<i>[Door Slams]</i>

01:53:24.458 --> 01:53:27.588
Excuse me, Dawson. Could you put me through
to Mr Helpmann's office, please?

01:53:27.628 --> 01:53:29.528
I'm afraid I can't, sir.

01:53:29.630 --> 01:53:32.593
<i>–[Elevator Bell Dings]
–You have to go through the proper channels.</i>

01:53:32.633 --> 01:53:38.098
And you can't tell me what
the proper channels are
because that's classified information.

01:53:38.138 --> 01:53:43.604
I'm glad to see the ministry is continuing
its tradition of recruiting
the brightest and best, sir.

01:53:43.644 --> 01:53:45.612
Thank you, Dawson.

01:53:47.648 --> 01:53:49.878
<i>[Elevator Bell Dings]</i>

01:53:49.984 --> 01:53:52.384
[Sam Groans]

01:53:52.486 --> 01:53:56.314
<i>–[Dawson] Good night, Mr Lime.
–Good night, Dawson.</i>

01:54:09.169 --> 01:54:12.764
<i>[Men Singing]
♫The first Noel ♫</i>

01:54:12.873 --> 01:54:16.138
<i>♫ The angels did say ♫</i>

01:54:16.243 --> 01:54:19.542
<i>♫ Was to certain poor shepherds ♫</i>

01:54:19.647 --> 01:54:23.043
<i>–♫ In fields as they lay ♫
–♫ [Man Singing Out Of Turn]</i>

01:54:23.083 --> 01:54:26.314
<i>♫ In fields where they ♫</i>

01:54:26.420 --> 01:54:28.320
No, no, no, Arthur!

01:54:28.422 --> 01:54:30.322
You're flat on the “G.”

01:54:30.424 --> 01:54:33.854
It's your breathing.
Now take a deep breath after “Noel.”

01:54:33.894 --> 01:54:36.055
Ready? One, two, three.

01:54:36.163 --> 01:54:38.723
♫The first Noel ♫

01:54:39.733 --> 01:54:42.566
<i>♫ The angels did say ♫</i>

01:54:47.308 --> 01:54:51.642
<i>[Helpmann's Voice]
'Ere I am, J.H.</i>

01:54:51.745 --> 01:54:54.375
<i>–The ghost in the machine.
–[Beeping]</i>

01:54:54.415 --> 01:54:58.112
E-R-E-I-A-M-J-H.

01:55:20.908 --> 01:55:22.876
Mr Helpmann.

01:55:32.086 --> 01:55:34.054
Mr Helpmann.

01:56:00.347 --> 01:56:02.315
Mr Helpmann?

01:57:07.681 --> 01:57:10.650
[Typing]

01:57:25.199 --> 01:57:27.167
Jill.

01:57:29.536 --> 01:57:31.504
Jill?

01:57:45.953 --> 01:57:47.921
Jill?

01:58:16.984 --> 01:58:18.952
Who's there?

01:58:19.052 --> 01:58:21.520
[No Audible Dialogue]

01:58:28.262 --> 01:58:30.822
What do you think?

01:58:30.931 --> 01:58:33.161
Is it me?

01:58:38.705 --> 01:58:40.673
Well?

01:58:45.612 --> 01:58:48.513
You don't exist anymore.

01:58:48.615 --> 01:58:50.583
I've killed you.

01:58:54.988 --> 01:58:56.956
Jill Layton is dead.

01:59:05.632 --> 01:59:08.328
Care for a little necrophilia?

01:59:08.435 --> 01:59:10.403
Hmm?

01:59:12.239 --> 01:59:14.366
Yee-hah! Yee-hah!

02:00:11.365 --> 02:00:13.959
[Clears Throat]
Merry Christmas.

02:00:15.068 --> 02:00:17.036
Uh—

02:00:25.045 --> 02:00:27.275
[Jill Giggling]

02:00:27.381 --> 02:00:30.087
<i>[Jill]
Something for an executive?</i>

02:00:36.923 --> 02:00:39.551
<i>[Alarm Blaring]</i>

02:00:41.728 --> 02:00:44.993
<i>[Male Voice on Speaker, Distorted]</i>

02:00:45.098 --> 02:00:47.498
[Sam Whimpering, Stammering]

02:00:47.601 --> 02:00:50.661
Sh-She's dead.
This is just a friend of mine.

02:00:50.771 --> 02:00:53.734
<i>–[Stammering] She's—
–[Male Voice Continues]</i>

02:00:53.774 --> 02:00:55.674
–What are you—
–No!

02:00:55.776 --> 02:00:57.767
–Oh, my God!
–No! Sam!

02:00:57.878 --> 02:01:01.678
<i>–[Machine Gun Fire]
–[Wheels Squeaking]</i>

02:01:01.882 --> 02:01:04.783
<i>[Uneven Breathing]</i>

02:01:04.885 --> 02:01:08.150
“N3/HK/608, you are charged
with the following:

02:01:08.255 --> 02:01:11.251
<i>“giving aid and comfort
to the enemies of society,</i>

02:01:11.291 --> 02:01:13.253
“attempting to conceal
a fugitive from justice;

02:01:13.293 --> 02:01:15.522
“passing confidential documents
to unauthorized personnel…

02:01:15.562 --> 02:01:17.524
“viz I.R dossier Jillian Layton;

02:01:17.564 --> 02:01:20.527
“destroying government property viz
an indeterminate number of personnel carriers;

02:01:20.567 --> 02:01:23.263
“taking possession under false pretenses
of said personnel carriers;

02:01:23.303 --> 02:01:26.166
“forging the signature
of the head of Records, third department;

02:01:26.206 --> 02:01:29.770
“intention to misdirect ministry funds
to the form of a check to A. Buttle…

02:01:29.810 --> 02:01:31.772
“through unauthorized channels;

02:01:31.812 --> 02:01:33.774
“tampering Central Services
supply ducts;

02:01:33.814 --> 02:01:36.276
“obstruction of forces, Law and Order,
in the exercise of their duty;

02:01:36.316 --> 02:01:37.778
“bringing into disrepute
the good name of the government…

02:01:37.818 --> 02:01:40.914
“and the standing within the community
of the Department of Information Retrieval;

02:01:40.954 --> 02:01:46.219
“attempting to disrupt the
Ministry of Information
Retrieval's internal communicating system;

02:01:46.259 --> 02:01:48.437
wasting ministry time and paper.”

02:01:48.462 --> 02:01:51.058
<i>–[Sam Exhales]
–Now, either you plead guilty…</i>

02:01:51.098 --> 02:01:53.060
to, say, seven or eight of the charges…

02:01:53.100 --> 02:01:56.530
which is going to help keep costs down
within your means…

02:01:56.570 --> 02:02:00.767
or you can borrow a sum, to be negotiated
from us, at a very competitive rate.

02:02:00.807 --> 02:02:04.271
We can offer you something,
let's say 11 and a half percent over 30 years…

02:02:04.311 --> 02:02:07.274
but you will have to buy insurance
to qualify for this scheme.

02:02:07.314 --> 02:02:09.876
Or, if you prefer something
more specific…

02:02:09.916 --> 02:02:12.622
say, against electrical charges
over £70—

02:02:12.652 --> 02:02:15.782
All you're requested to do at this stage
is to sign this form.

02:02:15.822 --> 02:02:18.218
<i>–[Women Screaming]
–[Echoing] Think carefully before you decide.</i>

02:02:18.258 --> 02:02:21.054
Looking ahead in financial matters
is always a wise course.

02:02:21.094 --> 02:02:24.592
<i>–[Men's Voices Overlapping]
–[Women Screaming]</i>

02:02:29.002 --> 02:02:32.597
Sam, what are we going to do with you?

02:02:34.674 --> 02:02:36.642
Where is Jill?

02:02:38.345 --> 02:02:40.404
I've got to find her.

02:02:40.514 --> 02:02:43.748
Please. Please, you've got to
get me out of here.

02:02:43.850 --> 02:02:47.377
I understand, Sam.
I know exactly how you feel.

02:02:47.487 --> 02:02:50.979
So I've brought you
a bottle of barley water.

02:02:51.091 --> 02:02:53.753
Oh, please help me.

02:02:53.860 --> 02:02:57.324
I assure you, Sam,
I'm doing everything within my power.

02:02:57.364 --> 02:03:00.299
But the rules of the game
are laid down.

02:03:00.400 --> 02:03:03.369
We all have to play by them.
Even me.

02:03:04.538 --> 02:03:08.702
[Stammers] It's all a mistake.
You've got to understand that.

02:03:08.809 --> 02:03:14.107
Yes, well, from the department's point of view,
you're certainly a bit of an own goal, but—

02:03:14.147 --> 02:03:16.809
I'm not a terrorist.

02:03:16.917 --> 02:03:19.880
You must know that.
Please, please get me out of here.

02:03:19.920 --> 02:03:23.378
Sam, information retrieval
is expensive.

02:03:23.490 --> 02:03:26.486
You're running up an enormous bill
by not cooperating.

02:03:26.526 --> 02:03:28.687
Please.

02:03:28.795 --> 02:03:31.764
Please, Mr Helpmann.

02:03:31.865 --> 02:03:33.833
Help me find Jill.

02:03:35.302 --> 02:03:37.202
Jill.

02:03:37.304 --> 02:03:39.295
Yes.

02:03:39.406 --> 02:03:42.637
Sam, I think I ought to tell you.

02:03:42.742 --> 02:03:47.338
I'm afraid she's upped stumps
and retired to the pavilion.

02:03:49.182 --> 02:03:51.150
<i>Thrown in the towel.</i>

02:03:52.352 --> 02:03:54.252
Dead?

02:03:54.354 --> 02:03:56.447
Yes.

02:03:56.556 --> 02:03:59.586
It's all a bit confusing,
but it seems she was killed…

02:03:59.626 --> 02:04:01.594
resisting arrest.

02:04:04.631 --> 02:04:07.623
No. It's all right.

02:04:07.734 --> 02:04:09.702
I did that.

02:04:12.372 --> 02:04:15.335
The odd thing is,
it appears to have happened twice.

02:04:15.375 --> 02:04:17.685
Bit of a disputed call, I'm afraid.

02:04:20.180 --> 02:04:22.148
Twice?

02:04:22.249 --> 02:04:24.149
So, there you are.

02:04:24.251 --> 02:04:29.082
All I can say is, don't fall at the last fence,
the finishing post in sight.

02:04:29.122 --> 02:04:31.022
See you in the paddock.

02:04:31.124 --> 02:04:33.524
Do cooperate.
Think of your mother.

02:04:33.627 --> 02:04:36.069
Good luck.
Keep your eye on the ball.

02:04:36.129 --> 02:04:39.530
Gotta go.
Can't keep the orphans waiting.

02:04:40.567 --> 02:04:44.025
<i>[Sleigh Bells Jingling]</i>

02:04:46.973 --> 02:04:49.703
<i>[Gasping, Shouting]</i>

02:05:04.157 --> 02:05:06.216
[Gasps]

02:05:07.661 --> 02:05:09.754
Don't fight it, son.

02:05:09.863 --> 02:05:11.922
Confess quickly.

02:05:13.066 --> 02:05:17.422
If you hold out too long,
you could jeopardize your credit rating.

02:05:18.838 --> 02:05:21.306
[Gasping, Whimpering]

02:05:28.148 --> 02:05:30.048
695/6.

02:05:30.150 --> 02:05:32.880
<i>–[Sam Trembling]
–Thank you.</i>

02:06:06.519 --> 02:06:08.783
Jack?

02:06:13.994 --> 02:06:16.087
Jack.

02:06:16.196 --> 02:06:18.289
Jack. Jack!

02:06:18.398 --> 02:06:20.298
Shut up.

02:06:20.400 --> 02:06:23.597
Jack. Jack, I'm innocent.
Please.

02:06:23.703 --> 02:06:25.967
–Help me.
–Bastard.

02:06:27.207 --> 02:06:28.902
Jack.

02:06:29.009 --> 02:06:31.781
Jack, this is all a mistake.
Please, Jack.

02:06:31.811 --> 02:06:33.779
Take that mask off.

02:06:35.648 --> 02:06:37.616
<i>[Feedback]</i>

02:06:38.952 --> 02:06:40.920
You stupid bastard.

02:06:42.188 --> 02:06:44.622
–Jack.
–How could you do this to me?

02:06:44.724 --> 02:06:46.624
Jack, I'm frightened.

02:06:46.726 --> 02:06:48.970
How do you think I feel, you shit?

02:06:49.062 --> 02:06:51.030
–Jack-
–Shut up!

02:06:52.565 --> 02:06:55.432
<i>[Feedback]</i>

02:06:55.535 --> 02:06:59.869
This is a professional relationship.

02:07:00.974 --> 02:07:02.874
Jack.

02:07:02.976 --> 02:07:06.173
[Trembling]
Jack, no, you can't.

02:07:06.279 --> 02:07:08.839
[Gasps]
No, Jack, please.

02:07:08.948 --> 02:07:11.041
<i>Jack, no! Don't!</i>

02:07:11.151 --> 02:07:13.619
<i>Please, Jack! No!</i>

02:07:13.720 --> 02:07:16.848
<i>[Gunshot]</i>

02:07:21.795 --> 02:07:24.263
[Gasping]

02:07:31.704 --> 02:07:33.672
[Groans]

02:07:58.698 --> 02:08:01.690
–You okay?
–Tuttle!

02:08:01.801 --> 02:08:03.769
Call me Harry.

02:08:18.318 --> 02:08:20.479
[Screams]

02:08:49.382 --> 02:08:51.282
<i>[Elevator Bell Dings]</i>

02:08:51.384 --> 02:08:53.682
Let's go!

02:09:09.536 --> 02:09:12.232
[Frequencies Tuning, Beeping]

02:09:24.250 --> 02:09:25.683
Here. Here.

02:09:46.873 --> 02:09:49.205
[Screams]

02:10:25.612 --> 02:10:28.547
[Sirens Wailing]

02:11:01.848 --> 02:11:04.578
[Shouting, Laughing]

02:11:07.954 --> 02:11:10.923
[Shouting Continues]

02:13:15.515 --> 02:13:18.848
<i>[Male Voice On Speaker, Distorted]</i>

02:14:02.929 --> 02:14:06.763
Ah, Mr Lowry.
So pleased you could make it.

02:14:06.866 --> 02:14:09.130
Right this way.

02:14:13.639 --> 02:14:15.607
It's a sad loss.

02:14:15.708 --> 02:14:18.471
<i>Your mother was with her at the end.</i>

02:14:18.511 --> 02:14:22.743
[Minister]
The gift of eternal life.

02:14:22.849 --> 02:14:27.980
Mrs Terrain has just received
that most wonderful of gifts.

02:14:28.087 --> 02:14:30.450
<i>She came to us physically new.</i>

02:14:30.490 --> 02:14:34.551
<i>She goes hence from us
not so physically new.</i>

02:14:34.660 --> 02:14:36.622
But the spirit never grows old.

02:14:36.662 --> 02:14:39.756
[Clears Throat]
Madame Lowry.

02:14:39.866 --> 02:14:42.061
[Giggling]

02:14:44.103 --> 02:14:46.071
Mother.

02:14:47.373 --> 02:14:49.273
[Ida's Voice]
Oh. Sam.

02:14:49.375 --> 02:14:51.843
Mother. Mother!

02:14:54.013 --> 02:14:56.243
Stop calling me that.

02:14:57.283 --> 02:15:00.684
Mother! Mother, please!

02:15:00.786 --> 02:15:04.218
–Is this guy bothering you?
–Oh. Tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk.

02:15:04.257 --> 02:15:07.090
Mother!

02:15:07.193 --> 02:15:11.254
Go away.
This is a very sacred moment.

02:15:11.364 --> 02:15:13.832
[Giggling]

02:15:13.933 --> 02:15:15.594
<i>[Explosion]</i>

02:15:18.004 --> 02:15:20.871
<i>[Male Voice On Speaker, Distorted]</i>

02:15:56.676 --> 02:15:59.042
[Screaming]

02:16:40.519 --> 02:16:43.579
<i>[Screeching]</i>

02:16:50.396 --> 02:16:53.092
[Grunting]

02:17:26.599 --> 02:17:28.566
[No Audible Dialogue]

02:18:20.786 --> 02:18:22.947
He's got away from us, Jack.

02:18:23.055 --> 02:18:25.352
Afraid you're right, Mr Helpmann.

02:18:25.458 --> 02:18:28.018
He's gone.

02:18:28.127 --> 02:18:30.561
Mmm.

02:18:30.663 --> 02:18:32.630
Well—

02:18:37.870 --> 02:18:41.829
♫ [Humming “Brazil”]

02:18:52.518 --> 02:18:55.180
♫ [Humming Grows Louder]

02:19:00.959 --> 02:19:04.293
♫ [Humming Continues]

02:19:04.396 --> 02:19:07.263
<i>[Man]
♫Then ♫</i>

02:19:07.366 --> 02:19:12.736
<i>♫ Tomorrow was another day ♫</i>

02:19:12.838 --> 02:19:17.138
<i>♫ The morning found me miles away ♫</i>

02:19:18.177 --> 02:19:23.478
<i>♫ With still a million things to say ♫</i>

02:19:25.918 --> 02:19:28.785
<i>♫ Now ♫</i>

02:19:28.888 --> 02:19:32.984
<i>♫ As twilight gleams the sky above ♫</i>

02:19:34.192 --> 02:19:38.459
<i>♫ Recalling thrills of our love ♫</i>

02:19:39.799 --> 02:19:44.168
<i>♫ There's one thing I'm certain of♫</i>

02:19:44.270 --> 02:19:47.171
<i>♫ Return ♫</i>

02:19:47.272 --> 02:19:50.071
<i>♫ I will ♫</i>

02:19:50.176 --> 02:19:53.634
<i>♫ To old ♫</i>

02:19:53.746 --> 02:19:58.274
<i>♫ Brazil ♫</i>

02:20:00.019 --> 02:20:03.978
<i>–[Revelers Shouting, Laughing]
–♫ [Samba]</i>

02:20:06.192 --> 02:20:10.218
<i>–♫ [Samba, Orchestra: “Brazil”]
–♫ [Chorus Vocalizing]</i>

02:22:39.211 --> 02:22:42.669
<i>♫ [Fades]</i>

